WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:25.233 --> 00:00:27.235
[ocean waves crashing]

3
00:00:38.747 --> 00:00:41.082
[moaning]

4
00:00:50.967 --> 00:00:51.968
[moans]

5
00:00:55.221 --> 00:00:56.181
[moans]

6
00:00:57.098 --> 00:00:58.808
[woman] What are you doing here?

7
00:00:58.892 --> 00:01:01.936
What's wrong?
Why aren't you sleeping in your room?

8
00:01:03.021 --> 00:01:05.106
[boy gasps]

9
00:01:05.190 --> 00:01:08.735
I was practicing how to swim.
I meant dive. not swim.

10
00:01:08.818 --> 00:01:12.030
Okay. Dive all you want. Ja-in.
Just let me sleep.

11
00:01:13.281 --> 00:01:15.658
Everything outside's a swimming pool now!

12
00:01:15.742 --> 00:01:17.994
-So can we go swimming. Mom? Please?
-[groans]

13
00:01:18.078 --> 00:01:20.413
-Let's go swimming!
-Why do you always want to go swimming?

14
00:01:20.497 --> 00:01:22.999
And I told you
not to wear those goggles at home.

15
00:01:23.083 --> 00:01:25.043
They make your face look ugly.

16
00:01:26.461 --> 00:01:29.964
I wanna swim outside. not here.
I'm telling you.

17
00:01:30.048 --> 00:01:32.383
There's a real swimming pool outside now.

18
00:01:32.467 --> 00:01:35.011
Come on!
Can't you just skip work this time?

19
00:01:35.095 --> 00:01:36.596
-[mother] Ja-in. get up.
-[whines]

20
00:01:36.679 --> 00:01:39.349
{\an8}You can't ditch kindergarten.
and I can't ditch work.

21
00:01:39.432 --> 00:01:42.435
{\an8}[whines] No. let me just do one more dive.

22
00:01:42.519 --> 00:01:45.647
{\an8}We can do it together. okay?
Please? Please?

23
00:01:45.730 --> 00:01:49.150
{\an8}[sighs] You dive. and I'll count. okay?

24
00:01:49.234 --> 00:01:51.111
[Ja-in] Count to 30 for me. okay?

25
00:01:51.611 --> 00:01:52.612
[mother moans]

26
00:01:53.321 --> 00:01:54.405
[mother] All right.

27
00:01:54.489 --> 00:01:55.573
One.

28
00:01:56.366 --> 00:01:57.575
Two.

29
00:01:58.576 --> 00:01:59.744
[yawns] Three.

30
00:02:00.870 --> 00:02:01.996
Four.

31
00:02:02.997 --> 00:02:04.332
Five.

32
00:02:05.291 --> 00:02:06.709
Six.

33
00:02:07.961 --> 00:02:09.337
Seven.

34
00:02:09.420 --> 00:02:10.880
[Ja-in breathing heavily]

35
00:02:13.550 --> 00:02:18.054
-You know you can't breathe while diving.
-[Ja-in. nasally] I wasn't breathing.

36
00:02:18.138 --> 00:02:20.682
I've been holding my breath
this whole time.

37
00:02:20.765 --> 00:02:22.725
-Hurry up and keep counting.
-[sighs]

38
00:02:23.309 --> 00:02:24.394
Eight.

39
00:02:25.603 --> 00:02:26.563
Nine.

40
00:02:27.063 --> 00:02:29.065
[thunder rumbling]

41
00:02:34.028 --> 00:02:34.946
Huh?

42
00:02:36.197 --> 00:02:38.199
[thunder rumbling]

43
00:02:39.159 --> 00:02:40.160
[groans]

44
00:02:52.672 --> 00:02:54.674
[thunder rumbling]

45
00:02:58.803 --> 00:03:01.890
[mother] Ja-in. remember
to take your medicine after breakfast.

46
00:03:01.973 --> 00:03:03.933
Don't forget. because Mommy might.

47
00:03:04.017 --> 00:03:08.354
Mom. can I borrow that screen thingy
you use for work so I can draw something?

48
00:03:08.438 --> 00:03:11.941
Why do you always wanna draw on that. hmm?
What about your sketchbooks?

49
00:03:12.025 --> 00:03:15.695
'Cause you never look at it
when I draw in my sketchbook.

50
00:03:16.279 --> 00:03:18.031
What do you mean by that?

51
00:03:24.913 --> 00:03:26.664
It's on the bed. You can go get it.

52
00:03:29.918 --> 00:03:32.170
-[Ja-in] Mom! Mom!
-Yeah?

53
00:03:33.296 --> 00:03:36.007
[Ja-in] The password thingy
isn't popping up.

54
00:03:36.090 --> 00:03:37.550
[mother] Again? Oh! [grunts]

55
00:03:39.219 --> 00:03:41.554
-Hey!
-[phone ringing]

56
00:03:41.638 --> 00:03:43.806
[woman] <i>It's raining so much.</i>
<i>What are you going to do?</i>

57
00:03:43.890 --> 00:03:46.893
What do you mean?
I'll just take the day off.

58
00:03:47.393 --> 00:03:49.312
How about you? Raining a lot there too?

59
00:03:49.395 --> 00:03:51.481
[sighs] <i>My goodness. it's pouring.</i>

60
00:03:51.564 --> 00:03:53.775
Grandma! I miss you!

61
00:03:53.858 --> 00:03:55.360
-Move over there.
-How are you?

62
00:03:55.443 --> 00:03:56.945
-Can you come visit us again?
-Ja-in!

63
00:03:57.028 --> 00:03:59.155
<i>…I brought you last time</i>
<i>so you can make some soup.</i>

64
00:03:59.239 --> 00:04:00.073
[groans]

65
00:04:01.115 --> 00:04:03.201
[mother] I didn't even know we had this.

66
00:04:03.284 --> 00:04:04.661
<i>Miyeokguk </i>sounds good.

67
00:04:04.744 --> 00:04:08.039
<i>Make sure it's moist when you stir-fry it.</i>
<i>And stop eating out so much.</i>

68
00:04:08.122 --> 00:04:10.959
<i>It's not real food.</i>
<i>and you need to take care of yourself.</i>

69
00:04:11.042 --> 00:04:13.795
<i>You think you're fine now.</i>
<i>but you'll get sick when you're older.</i>

70
00:04:13.878 --> 00:04:17.548
Mom. that's why
I'm making breakfast right now.

71
00:04:17.632 --> 00:04:19.884
<i>I'll drop by</i>
<i>with fresh ingredients next week.</i>

72
00:04:19.968 --> 00:04:22.637
<i>So don't skip meals.</i>
<i>and eat properly. all right?</i>

73
00:04:22.720 --> 00:04:24.681
[sighs] <i>My goodness.</i>
<i>When I see the things you eat…</i>

74
00:04:24.764 --> 00:04:26.808
<i>-I should move in--</i>
-I heard you. I have another call.

75
00:04:26.891 --> 00:04:29.060
Gotta hang up.
I'll talk to you later. okay?

76
00:04:29.143 --> 00:04:31.145
<i>All right. Oh. by the way. An-na--</i>

77
00:04:36.109 --> 00:04:37.068
[An-na sighs]

78
00:04:38.111 --> 00:04:40.113
[water rushing]

79
00:04:50.081 --> 00:04:53.167
Shin Ja-in.
is the water running in the bathroom?

80
00:04:53.751 --> 00:04:55.962
I don't think so.
I didn't go to the bathroom.

81
00:04:57.672 --> 00:04:58.715
Okay.

82
00:04:58.798 --> 00:05:01.134
Mom. I just drew this for you.

83
00:05:02.135 --> 00:05:03.469
What is it?

84
00:05:03.553 --> 00:05:04.846
[Ja-in] Mommy and me.

85
00:05:06.723 --> 00:05:07.598
[tuts]

86
00:05:08.141 --> 00:05:09.100
Ja-in.

87
00:05:10.351 --> 00:05:13.438
If you're gonna draw me.
can you at least make me look nice?

88
00:05:13.521 --> 00:05:14.856
What do you mean?

89
00:05:15.356 --> 00:05:17.984
You've got other colors
like red and green. right?

90
00:05:18.067 --> 00:05:19.986
-Don't just use black. What the…
-[water sloshes]

91
00:05:26.659 --> 00:05:28.661
[ominous music playing]

92
00:05:48.181 --> 00:05:50.183
[ocean waves crashing]

93
00:05:52.518 --> 00:05:55.188
[breathing nervously]

94
00:05:58.358 --> 00:05:59.650
[announcement tone plays]

95
00:05:59.734 --> 00:06:02.528
Mom. our house really has turned
into a swimming pool!

96
00:06:02.612 --> 00:06:04.447
[woman] <i>This is an announcement</i>
<i>from management.</i>

97
00:06:04.530 --> 00:06:05.823
[An-na] Can you keep quiet?

98
00:06:05.907 --> 00:06:08.242
<i>Due to the record-breaking heavy rain.</i>

99
00:06:08.326 --> 00:06:12.538
<i>buildings 101 through 107</i>
<i>have flooded up to the second floor.</i>

100
00:06:12.622 --> 00:06:16.626
<i>and buildings 108 through 110</i>
<i>have flooded up to the third floor.</i>

101
00:06:17.126 --> 00:06:19.754
<i>-Residents on the affected floors…</i>
-Mom. let's swim together!

102
00:06:19.837 --> 00:06:21.589
-Can we swim at home?
-Ja-in. wait a minute!

103
00:06:21.672 --> 00:06:23.466
Why? Why? I wanna play right now.

104
00:06:23.549 --> 00:06:26.761
You promised we were going to play.
so why can't we?

105
00:06:26.844 --> 00:06:30.640
-Shin Ja-in! I said be quiet!
<i>-Elevators have been temporarily disabled.</i>

106
00:06:30.723 --> 00:06:33.142
<i>Please evacuate immediately.</i>

107
00:06:33.226 --> 00:06:35.353
[Ja-in] Come on!
We were supposed to swim together!

108
00:06:35.436 --> 00:06:38.398
-I wanna swim!
-Shin Ja-in. why aren't you listening?

109
00:06:38.481 --> 00:06:40.024
<i>…record-breaking rainfall…</i>

110
00:06:40.108 --> 00:06:42.568
Didn't Mommy tell you
not to wear these inside the house?

111
00:06:43.069 --> 00:06:45.863
Stay right here.
or you're not getting them back again!

112
00:06:45.947 --> 00:06:48.449
[announcement continues indistinctly]

113
00:06:49.242 --> 00:06:51.244
[breathing nervously]

114
00:06:51.327 --> 00:06:53.329
[uneasy music playing]

115
00:06:59.377 --> 00:07:01.379
[phone ringing]

116
00:07:04.424 --> 00:07:05.258
Hello?

117
00:07:05.341 --> 00:07:08.010
<i>This is Son Hee-jo from</i>
<i>Darwin Center's Personnel Security Team.</i>

118
00:07:08.094 --> 00:07:10.805
<i>Are you the manager of</i>
<i>the Emotion Engine Development Team 3?</i>

119
00:07:10.888 --> 00:07:12.348
<i>-Is your home flooding?</i>
-Yes.

120
00:07:12.432 --> 00:07:15.476
<i>I'm coming to pick you up. Dr. Gu.</i>
<i>I'm almost at your apartment.</i>

121
00:07:16.060 --> 00:07:18.187
-My apartment?
<i>-The third floor will be flooded soon.</i>

122
00:07:18.271 --> 00:07:20.815
<i>Evacuate to the upper floors</i>
<i>as soon as possible.</i>

123
00:07:20.898 --> 00:07:24.026
<i>If you're packing now. just leave.</i>
<i>Don't be scared.</i>

124
00:07:24.861 --> 00:07:27.071
<i>Just come up the stairs with Ja-in.</i>
<i>and I'll fi--</i>

125
00:07:27.155 --> 00:07:28.072
Hello?

126
00:07:28.781 --> 00:07:29.699
Hello?

127
00:07:31.742 --> 00:07:33.744
[tense music playing]

128
00:07:48.342 --> 00:07:50.636
SHIN JA-IN (JULY. WEEK 2)

129
00:07:52.388 --> 00:07:53.431
[An-na] Ja-in!

130
00:07:56.225 --> 00:07:57.143
Ja-in!

131
00:07:57.643 --> 00:08:01.063
We need to leave right now!
Hurry up and get out here. okay?

132
00:08:04.025 --> 00:08:05.359
[panting]

133
00:08:06.569 --> 00:08:10.364
Ja-in. Let's go. We gotta go now!

134
00:08:11.282 --> 00:08:14.243
Ja-in. Mommy's sorry.
I was just a bit upset earlier.

135
00:08:14.327 --> 00:08:17.371
I'm not mad at you though.
Hey. want me to give you a ride?

136
00:08:19.499 --> 00:08:21.501
[distant siren wailing]

137
00:08:23.336 --> 00:08:24.587
[music intensifies]

138
00:08:24.670 --> 00:08:26.422
[An-na grunting. panting]

139
00:08:36.349 --> 00:08:37.767
[woman 1] Hurry up. honey!

140
00:08:40.144 --> 00:08:42.522
Don't cry. We have to hurry.

141
00:08:43.022 --> 00:08:44.732
-Hello.
-Hi there.

142
00:08:46.317 --> 00:08:48.194
-[man 1 grunts]
-Excuse me. Can we pass through?

143
00:08:48.277 --> 00:08:50.780
[woman 1] How can we take all that
and the kids?

144
00:08:50.863 --> 00:08:52.406
[man 1] It's fine. We should hurry.

145
00:08:52.490 --> 00:08:55.034
[woman 1] Gyun-a. stop crying.
We need to hurry.

146
00:08:55.117 --> 00:08:57.161
Come on! Hurry up! Let's go!

147
00:08:59.038 --> 00:09:01.457
[man 2] Ji-a. it's dangerous.
so keep holding Daddy's hand.

148
00:09:01.541 --> 00:09:03.793
-[An-na] Excuse me.
-[man 2] I told you to stay put!

149
00:09:03.876 --> 00:09:06.128
-[An-na] Excuse me.
-[man 3] How did the water get up here?

150
00:09:06.629 --> 00:09:07.964
-[man 2] Ji-a!
-[An-na] Sir. can I…

151
00:09:08.047 --> 00:09:11.217
[man 4] Honey. just check on the kids.
I'm gonna go figure it out.

152
00:09:11.300 --> 00:09:12.843
[man 5] Why is no one moving?

153
00:09:12.927 --> 00:09:14.595
[man 6] Seriously. stop pushing!

154
00:09:14.679 --> 00:09:16.138
[An-na] Excuse me.

155
00:09:16.222 --> 00:09:17.890
Why is no one moving?

156
00:09:17.974 --> 00:09:20.935
Huh? I'm not really sure.

157
00:09:21.018 --> 00:09:24.272
-Someone got stuck or something like that.
-He collapsed.

158
00:09:24.355 --> 00:09:27.275
[woman 2] Believe in our Lord Jesus
so you and your family will be saved.

159
00:09:27.358 --> 00:09:28.568
[man 7] Just go already!

160
00:09:28.651 --> 00:09:30.069
[An-na] So sorry. Coming through.

161
00:09:30.653 --> 00:09:33.489
Please. Lord. Only you can deliver us
from this terrible fate.

162
00:09:33.573 --> 00:09:35.575
[An-na panting]

163
00:09:35.658 --> 00:09:37.660
[residents clamoring]

164
00:09:38.911 --> 00:09:40.997
[man 8] Auntie. open the door already!

165
00:09:41.080 --> 00:09:42.999
[woman 1] Min-jun. hurry! Go!

166
00:09:43.082 --> 00:09:44.542
[boy crying]

167
00:09:47.169 --> 00:09:48.421
[man 9] Someone help us!

168
00:09:49.171 --> 00:09:51.132
[residents screaming. clamoring]

169
00:09:51.215 --> 00:09:53.092
[tense ethereal music playing]

170
00:09:54.010 --> 00:09:55.636
[thunder rumbling]

171
00:09:55.720 --> 00:10:01.267
{\an8}PRESENT DAY. SEOUL

172
00:10:13.446 --> 00:10:15.448
[footsteps splashing]

173
00:10:21.287 --> 00:10:22.455
[An-na grunts]

174
00:10:25.583 --> 00:10:27.585
[An-na panting]

175
00:10:34.342 --> 00:10:36.093
Are you scared. Ja-in?

176
00:10:36.177 --> 00:10:38.387
[Ja-in] I thought it was just water.

177
00:10:38.929 --> 00:10:41.182
but it looks like we can't swim in it.

178
00:10:42.266 --> 00:10:45.144
How about we sing a song together?

179
00:10:45.770 --> 00:10:49.231
We were gonna… gonna play together
regardless. right?

180
00:10:49.315 --> 00:10:50.608
All day long?

181
00:10:50.691 --> 00:10:52.193
[Ja-in] Regardless?

182
00:10:53.194 --> 00:10:55.196
What does "regardless" mean?

183
00:10:55.946 --> 00:10:57.698
"Regardless" is a word that means…

184
00:10:57.782 --> 00:10:59.659
Mom! Look over there!

185
00:11:00.159 --> 00:11:02.578
-Help!
-Someone help!

186
00:11:02.662 --> 00:11:05.206
-Help!
-Somebody help us!

187
00:11:07.291 --> 00:11:08.292
[An-na gasps]

188
00:11:12.588 --> 00:11:17.885
[in Korean] <i>♪ Along the Milky Way</i>
<i>In the blue sky ♪</i>

189
00:11:18.928 --> 00:11:22.848
<i>♪ A little white boat drifting by ♪</i>

190
00:11:24.100 --> 00:11:29.021
[both] <i>♪ With a single laurel tree ♪</i>

191
00:11:29.730 --> 00:11:34.318
<i>♪ There sits one tiny hare ♪</i>

192
00:11:34.860 --> 00:11:39.657
<i>♪ No mast upon the boat ♪</i>

193
00:11:40.199 --> 00:11:44.120
<i>♪ No paddle to keep it afloat ♪</i>

194
00:11:45.037 --> 00:11:49.583
<i>♪ Yet still it drifts on ♪</i>

195
00:11:50.376 --> 00:11:51.377
[in English] Huh?

196
00:11:56.924 --> 00:11:57.883
[An-na] Ja-in.

197
00:11:58.801 --> 00:11:59.969
Just wait here a sec.

198
00:12:00.052 --> 00:12:02.138
Where are you going?

199
00:12:02.221 --> 00:12:05.391
Not going anywhere.
I'm just gonna take a look.

200
00:12:05.474 --> 00:12:07.476
[thunder rumbling]

201
00:12:10.604 --> 00:12:12.606
[breathing nervously]

202
00:12:19.905 --> 00:12:21.240
[tense music sting]

203
00:12:27.830 --> 00:12:31.959
[man 1] Look. we're from room 407!
Could we just use your bathroom. please?

204
00:12:32.042 --> 00:12:33.961
[indistinct chattering]

205
00:12:34.044 --> 00:12:36.797
-It's for the kids! Please open up!
-[woman 1] Is there anyone in there?

206
00:12:36.881 --> 00:12:39.550
Please. we need some water
to make baby formula!

207
00:12:39.633 --> 00:12:41.385
[man 2] Just let me through already.

208
00:12:41.469 --> 00:12:45.556
Um. if anyone needs to use the bathroom
or get some water. feel free to come in.

209
00:12:45.639 --> 00:12:47.433
-[woman 2] Thank you.
-[woman 3] Thank you.

210
00:12:47.516 --> 00:12:48.768
-Excuse me.
-[Hee-jo] Ms. Gu!

211
00:12:48.851 --> 00:12:52.021
-[woman 4] It's okay. This way.
-[Hee-jo] Ms. Gu. where are you? Ms. Gu!

212
00:12:52.730 --> 00:12:56.192
Oh! Over here! I'm over here!

213
00:12:58.527 --> 00:13:00.613
[man 3] Hey. man. we gotta keep going up.

214
00:13:01.405 --> 00:13:02.740
Ja-in. let's go.

215
00:13:03.616 --> 00:13:04.784
[man 4] Come on. stop pushing.

216
00:13:04.867 --> 00:13:06.410
-Ja-in.
-[man 4] We're all stuck here.

217
00:13:09.789 --> 00:13:11.999
[man 5] Coming through.
Sorry. Coming through.

218
00:13:12.082 --> 00:13:14.043
-Excuse me. Sorry.
-Of course.

219
00:13:14.126 --> 00:13:15.294
[residents clamoring]

220
00:13:15.377 --> 00:13:16.420
Ja-in?

221
00:13:17.922 --> 00:13:18.923
Excuse me.

222
00:13:19.757 --> 00:13:20.758
Excuse me.

223
00:13:21.258 --> 00:13:22.510
Shin Ja-in!

224
00:13:22.593 --> 00:13:26.180
[rumbling]

225
00:13:29.058 --> 00:13:31.060
[tense ethereal music playing]

226
00:13:42.696 --> 00:13:44.490
An-na. are you okay?

227
00:13:44.573 --> 00:13:45.658
[gasps]

228
00:13:47.284 --> 00:13:50.162
-[music swells]
-[residents scream]

229
00:13:50.955 --> 00:13:52.832
[ethereal music playing]

230
00:13:52.915 --> 00:13:54.333
[water burbling]

231
00:13:57.336 --> 00:13:59.338
[tense ethereal music playing]

232
00:14:44.216 --> 00:14:45.342
[gasps]

233
00:14:46.010 --> 00:14:47.011
[inhales sharply]

234
00:15:15.372 --> 00:15:17.374
[somber ethereal music continues]

235
00:15:26.926 --> 00:15:28.928
[An-na grunting]

236
00:15:29.845 --> 00:15:31.180
[grunting continues]

237
00:15:32.056 --> 00:15:34.058
[door handle thumping]

238
00:15:48.072 --> 00:15:50.074
[music fades]

239
00:15:54.411 --> 00:15:56.413
[hopeful ethereal music playing]

240
00:16:41.291 --> 00:16:43.293
[music intensifies]

241
00:16:45.587 --> 00:16:47.006
[music stops]

242
00:16:47.089 --> 00:16:49.425
[gasping. coughing]

243
00:16:51.343 --> 00:16:53.387
-[An-na] Ja-in.
-Pass him to me!

244
00:16:54.263 --> 00:16:56.265
[Hee-jo grunting]

245
00:16:58.100 --> 00:16:59.893
-[An-na grunts]
-[Hee-jo] He's not breathing.

246
00:16:59.977 --> 00:17:02.021
[An-na breathing nervously]

247
00:17:02.104 --> 00:17:03.480
[An-na whimpers]

248
00:17:03.981 --> 00:17:05.983
[Ja-in coughs]

249
00:17:07.484 --> 00:17:09.069
-Ja-in. Ja-in!
-[Ja-in sobs]

250
00:17:11.488 --> 00:17:12.990
Mommy!

251
00:17:13.073 --> 00:17:15.034
-[Ja-in crying]
-[An-na sobs happily]

252
00:17:23.751 --> 00:17:26.253
It's okay. It's all right.

253
00:17:28.714 --> 00:17:31.800
Thank you so much. Thank you so much.

254
00:17:31.884 --> 00:17:34.428
I'm Son Hee-jo. Personnel Security Team 1.

255
00:17:34.928 --> 00:17:36.263
Let me record this.

256
00:17:36.346 --> 00:17:38.348
[Ja-in crying]

257
00:17:39.224 --> 00:17:41.018
[Hee-jo] July 7th. 7:55 a.m.

258
00:17:41.101 --> 00:17:44.605
Confirmed the survival of
Research Lead Gu An-na and the child.

259
00:17:44.688 --> 00:17:45.856
We're moving now.

260
00:17:46.732 --> 00:17:48.901
All set. Let's go.

261
00:17:48.984 --> 00:17:50.861
-Hey. come on.
-[An-na] Uh…

262
00:17:51.653 --> 00:17:54.490
-[sobbing] Mommy. Mommy!
-Uh. let me carry him.

263
00:17:54.573 --> 00:17:55.783
I can carry him.

264
00:17:56.617 --> 00:17:59.286
-[Hee-jo] There's more stairs. you know?
-Yeah. it's okay.

265
00:18:02.414 --> 00:18:04.416
[An-na] Come on. Get on my back.

266
00:18:10.839 --> 00:18:14.009
Shin Ja-in. are you doing okay?
You feel better?

267
00:18:15.052 --> 00:18:20.808
[Ja-in] I thought Mommy left me
and went to that house all by yourself.

268
00:18:21.600 --> 00:18:23.560
Where would I go without you?

269
00:18:24.061 --> 00:18:27.064
[Ja-in] But then.
lots of water started coming in. and

270
00:18:27.940 --> 00:18:31.443
that scared me. and I started thinking
about what happened last time.

271
00:18:31.944 --> 00:18:34.279
Mom. you remember back when…

272
00:18:35.239 --> 00:18:40.077
back when our car fell into the water.
and then Dad…

273
00:18:40.160 --> 00:18:41.036
Ja-in.

274
00:18:41.537 --> 00:18:43.622
You wanna sing again like before?

275
00:18:44.123 --> 00:18:46.667
[Ja-in] I don't wanna. I'm too sad.

276
00:18:46.750 --> 00:18:49.878
I don't really feel like
singing right now.

277
00:18:50.587 --> 00:18:52.798
[An-na] All right. Get some rest. then.

278
00:18:52.881 --> 00:18:56.426
We're heading to the rooftop.
Company helicopter is on the way.

279
00:18:56.927 --> 00:18:58.220
First time riding one?

280
00:18:58.303 --> 00:19:01.723
The water tasted salty.
Is it supposed to taste like that?

281
00:19:01.807 --> 00:19:04.685
An asteroid hit Antarctica
around three hours ago.

282
00:19:04.768 --> 00:19:07.813
It melted all the ice
and caused the seawater to rise north.

283
00:19:07.896 --> 00:19:09.940
Half of Japan has been submerged already.

284
00:19:10.023 --> 00:19:12.734
and this whole 30-floor apartment
will be underwater soon.

285
00:19:12.818 --> 00:19:14.153
An asteroid hit?

286
00:19:14.945 --> 00:19:16.947
Wait. how could they not see it coming?

287
00:19:17.030 --> 00:19:19.658
They did.
They just didn't say anything about it.

288
00:19:20.159 --> 00:19:22.369
They couldn't stop it. Humanity is doomed.

289
00:19:25.205 --> 00:19:28.333
Wait. wait. wait a minute. Wait a…

290
00:19:29.293 --> 00:19:30.169
[sighs]

291
00:19:31.295 --> 00:19:34.047
Does that mean…
that mean we're all gonna die?

292
00:19:36.967 --> 00:19:37.885
[sighs]

293
00:19:38.886 --> 00:19:40.053
All these years.

294
00:19:40.137 --> 00:19:43.432
you thought you were just working
at an AI development lab. right?

295
00:19:43.515 --> 00:19:44.558
Not quite.

296
00:19:45.142 --> 00:19:47.895
It's up to you
to create a whole new mankind.

297
00:19:49.188 --> 00:19:51.523
What? How… how could I--

298
00:19:51.607 --> 00:19:54.776
There are only two researchers
who've developed the Emotion Engine for AI

299
00:19:54.860 --> 00:19:56.028
in the entire world.

300
00:19:56.111 --> 00:19:58.405
And our first choice
went missing this morning.

301
00:19:58.488 --> 00:20:01.700
That's right. your boss.
Chief Researcher Im Hyeon-mo.

302
00:20:01.783 --> 00:20:03.869
She and the child she was raising
got swept away.

303
00:20:04.536 --> 00:20:08.123
We presumed she didn't make it.
so… you're the next choice.

304
00:20:09.166 --> 00:20:12.502
Once the chopper gets you to the shelter.
they'll tell you what to do.

305
00:20:13.086 --> 00:20:16.048
Uh. wait. Hold on a sec. Hold on.

306
00:20:16.131 --> 00:20:17.424
What is it?

307
00:20:18.008 --> 00:20:20.969
I… I actually don't know
all that much about it.

308
00:20:21.053 --> 00:20:24.806
We built the Emotion Engine together.
but it was just for testing.

309
00:20:24.890 --> 00:20:27.059
And. uh. without Chief Im.
I'm afraid I'd--

310
00:20:27.142 --> 00:20:29.353
So then what? Cancel the chopper?

311
00:20:30.395 --> 00:20:32.481
The rest of the teams
have completed their research.

312
00:20:32.564 --> 00:20:36.068
They've built human-like bodies with
intelligence and the ability to reproduce.

313
00:20:36.151 --> 00:20:38.987
The only thing left is the Emotion Engine.
Do you understand?

314
00:20:39.071 --> 00:20:40.530
You're all we've got now.

315
00:20:41.365 --> 00:20:43.617
[breathing shakily]

316
00:20:44.576 --> 00:20:45.869
[Ja-in] Mom?

317
00:20:46.745 --> 00:20:47.663
Yeah?

318
00:20:48.455 --> 00:20:50.499
[Ja-in] I need to go poo-poo.

319
00:20:51.083 --> 00:20:52.334
[An-na] Uh. hold on.

320
00:20:55.003 --> 00:20:57.047
Did you poop just now?

321
00:20:57.130 --> 00:21:01.176
No. but I need to go
'cause I can't hold it anymore.

322
00:21:01.260 --> 00:21:05.681
Ah. I didn't see that coming.
Can he hold it? We don't have much time.

323
00:21:06.723 --> 00:21:09.226
[An-na panting]

324
00:21:09.309 --> 00:21:13.981
Ja-in. we don't have extra pants for you.
You're gonna have to hold it in. okay?

325
00:21:14.731 --> 00:21:16.608
[thunder rumbling]

326
00:21:22.906 --> 00:21:24.908
[An-na panting]

327
00:21:26.576 --> 00:21:28.662
Hurry up. There are no extra pants.

328
00:21:33.834 --> 00:21:36.044
[An-na] Ja-in. not yet. okay?

329
00:21:37.087 --> 00:21:38.964
Ja-in. Hey. Ja-in.

330
00:21:40.465 --> 00:21:41.466
Not yet.

331
00:21:42.551 --> 00:21:44.428
Hold it. Just a sec.

332
00:21:44.511 --> 00:21:46.513
[phone line ringing]

333
00:21:47.389 --> 00:21:49.474
-[clears throat]
-[ringing continues]

334
00:21:53.895 --> 00:21:55.105
[sighs]

335
00:21:55.188 --> 00:21:58.233
Hey. it's me. We're proceeding all right.

336
00:22:02.029 --> 00:22:03.989
No. not yet. Kid had to poop.

337
00:22:09.161 --> 00:22:10.620
Why would I tell her that?

338
00:22:11.872 --> 00:22:13.790
I mean. she's following along.

339
00:22:15.083 --> 00:22:16.126
[door opens]

340
00:22:17.127 --> 00:22:18.253
[door closes]

341
00:22:18.337 --> 00:22:20.756
Okay. We'll get going right away.

342
00:22:21.673 --> 00:22:22.674
[disconnect tone]

343
00:22:23.467 --> 00:22:24.384
The kid?

344
00:22:25.010 --> 00:22:26.762
He can finish on his own.

345
00:22:27.554 --> 00:22:31.266
He can wear these. You should change too.
They don't belong to anyone now.

346
00:22:33.435 --> 00:22:35.437
[thunder rumbling]

347
00:22:43.528 --> 00:22:45.906
[Hee-jo] So. this Emotion Engine.

348
00:22:46.656 --> 00:22:48.450
it has human emotions in it?

349
00:22:49.034 --> 00:22:50.702
Like feelings and stuff?

350
00:22:52.537 --> 00:22:53.622
Yeah.

351
00:22:54.498 --> 00:22:56.333
So it's basically a person. then?

352
00:22:59.920 --> 00:23:02.297
I don't get why you'd give it
human emotions though.

353
00:23:02.964 --> 00:23:04.674
We know what those are like.

354
00:23:04.758 --> 00:23:08.011
If it's a new type of human.
it doesn't need that stuff. [chuckles]

355
00:23:10.305 --> 00:23:11.765
What's wrong with emotion?

356
00:23:12.265 --> 00:23:14.267
[pensive music playing]

357
00:23:15.185 --> 00:23:18.355
Boarding the helicopter won't be too easy.

358
00:23:18.438 --> 00:23:22.067
People up there will be begging
and fighting to get on.

359
00:23:22.567 --> 00:23:25.404
Everyone will be too busy
to care about their families.

360
00:23:25.904 --> 00:23:27.406
And the funny thing is.

361
00:23:27.906 --> 00:23:31.993
you'll be pushing past all of them. too.
doing what it takes to get on.

362
00:23:32.911 --> 00:23:34.871
There's nothing wrong with that though.

363
00:23:35.372 --> 00:23:37.749
That's just how human emotions work.

364
00:23:42.796 --> 00:23:43.755
Can I…

365
00:23:44.548 --> 00:23:45.966
Can I use your phone?

366
00:23:46.591 --> 00:23:49.511
[An-na's mother] <i>If anything happens.</i>
<i>call me right away.</i>

367
00:23:49.594 --> 00:23:51.763
<i>I can't believe I said</i>
<i>the third floor was fine</i>

368
00:23:51.847 --> 00:23:53.390
<i>when you were apartment hunting.</i>

369
00:23:54.224 --> 00:23:55.434
[An-na] Don't say that.

370
00:23:56.977 --> 00:23:59.479
It's a relief to hear
that you evacuated. Mom.

371
00:24:01.398 --> 00:24:02.732
Careful. okay?

372
00:24:03.984 --> 00:24:05.902
-[water sloshing]
-[distant scream]

373
00:24:07.028 --> 00:24:10.031
<i>An-na. it's still flooding over here.</i>

374
00:24:11.074 --> 00:24:12.409
<i>Listen carefully.</i>

375
00:24:13.201 --> 00:24:17.539
<i>From this point on.</i>
<i>your father and I don't matter.</i>

376
00:24:18.290 --> 00:24:20.041
<i>Ja-in is all you've got.</i>

377
00:24:20.542 --> 00:24:21.626
<i>Remember that. okay?</i>

378
00:24:21.710 --> 00:24:22.794
[voice breaking] Mom.

379
00:24:24.171 --> 00:24:25.213
What do you mean?

380
00:24:25.297 --> 00:24:26.506
[poignant music playing]

381
00:24:26.590 --> 00:24:29.468
The rain's gonna stop soon. all right?
Don't worry.

382
00:24:31.052 --> 00:24:33.305
You gotta come by next week with the food.

383
00:24:35.140 --> 00:24:36.183
<i>An-na.</i>

384
00:24:37.309 --> 00:24:39.311
<i>Thank you for everything.</i>

385
00:24:40.145 --> 00:24:41.104
<i>I…</i>

386
00:24:43.273 --> 00:24:45.358
<i>I love you so much.</i>

387
00:24:48.153 --> 00:24:49.154
[An-na whimpers]

388
00:24:49.237 --> 00:24:51.239
[distant screaming continues]

389
00:24:52.949 --> 00:24:53.867
Mom?

390
00:24:56.870 --> 00:24:57.954
Me too.

391
00:24:58.038 --> 00:24:59.289
[water rushing]

392
00:24:59.372 --> 00:25:00.332
[disconnect tone]

393
00:25:03.251 --> 00:25:04.211
[sniffles]

394
00:25:07.339 --> 00:25:08.840
[Hee-jo] Are you done with the call?

395
00:25:10.383 --> 00:25:13.303
That was nice to see.
talking to your mother.

396
00:25:14.095 --> 00:25:15.180
It was touching.

397
00:25:16.223 --> 00:25:18.433
That's just how human emotions work.

398
00:25:18.975 --> 00:25:20.810
Not that you'd care about it.

399
00:25:22.854 --> 00:25:25.190
Yeah. I don't have anyone to call. so…

400
00:25:25.899 --> 00:25:28.610
Let's go. Water's reached the tenth floor.

401
00:25:29.236 --> 00:25:30.278
[loud bang]

402
00:25:31.112 --> 00:25:33.114
[rattling]

403
00:25:38.078 --> 00:25:40.080
[unsettling music playing]

404
00:25:42.249 --> 00:25:44.251
[rattling continues]

405
00:25:45.252 --> 00:25:46.253
[loud bang]

406
00:25:46.336 --> 00:25:48.213
[gas hissing]

407
00:25:48.797 --> 00:25:49.881
We need to get out!

408
00:25:49.965 --> 00:25:51.591
[coughs] Ja-in.

409
00:25:51.675 --> 00:25:53.677
[tense music playing]

410
00:26:02.143 --> 00:26:03.061
Let's go.

411
00:26:04.813 --> 00:26:06.898
-[An-na gasps. grunts]
-[glass shattering]

412
00:26:07.941 --> 00:26:09.067
[breathing nervously]

413
00:26:09.150 --> 00:26:10.151
Come on.

414
00:26:13.947 --> 00:26:14.948
[An-na gasps]

415
00:26:18.451 --> 00:26:19.494
[An-na coughs]

416
00:26:20.120 --> 00:26:21.329
Put these on first.

417
00:26:22.914 --> 00:26:25.250
-[Ja-in groans]
-[An-na coughs]

418
00:26:25.333 --> 00:26:28.336
Come on. Don't get scared now.
Let's go. Hand me the kid.

419
00:26:33.300 --> 00:26:35.552
[Hee-jo grunting]

420
00:26:37.554 --> 00:26:38.638
-Mom.
-Huh?

421
00:26:38.722 --> 00:26:40.682
The fire's really hot.

422
00:26:40.765 --> 00:26:42.350
I know. Ja-in. It's okay.

423
00:26:43.018 --> 00:26:46.229
We're going up now.
You have to hold on tight. okay?

424
00:26:47.480 --> 00:26:49.149
[An-na grunts]

425
00:26:51.735 --> 00:26:53.737
[tense music continues]

426
00:26:59.117 --> 00:27:01.119
[breathing nervously]

427
00:27:03.371 --> 00:27:05.332
[An-na grunting]

428
00:27:05.415 --> 00:27:07.250
-[Hee-jo] That's it. Push him up.
-Ja-in!

429
00:27:08.585 --> 00:27:11.379
Ja-in. you're gonna go
up there first. all right?

430
00:27:11.463 --> 00:27:13.673
[Ja-in whimpers] No. I don't want to!

431
00:27:13.757 --> 00:27:15.467
-No! No! Mommy!
-Mommy will be right up.

432
00:27:15.550 --> 00:27:18.261
-You go first. okay?
-Mommy! I'm scared! I don't want to!

433
00:27:18.345 --> 00:27:22.140
-Ja-in. it'll just be a moment.
-[cries] No! I don't wanna!

434
00:27:22.223 --> 00:27:23.350
-[An-na] Ja-in!
-Mommy!

435
00:27:23.433 --> 00:27:25.977
Mommy. I don't want to.

436
00:27:26.061 --> 00:27:29.731
Mommy! Mommy. please!

437
00:27:29.814 --> 00:27:31.358
Mommy!

438
00:27:31.441 --> 00:27:33.443
[water burbling]

439
00:27:39.157 --> 00:27:41.159
[ethereal music playing]

440
00:27:52.712 --> 00:27:54.339
[thud echoes]

441
00:27:54.422 --> 00:27:55.924
[music fades]

442
00:27:56.007 --> 00:27:58.009
[gasping]

443
00:28:01.763 --> 00:28:02.764
[Hee-jo] An-na!

444
00:28:04.182 --> 00:28:06.601
-An-na. are you all right?
-[Ja-in] Mom!

445
00:28:06.685 --> 00:28:08.228
-Yes!
-[Ja-in] Mommy!

446
00:28:08.311 --> 00:28:09.479
Mommy!

447
00:28:09.562 --> 00:28:12.232
No! It's okay
'cause Mommy's not going anywhere!

448
00:28:12.315 --> 00:28:14.067
-Mom! Mommy!
-[An-na] It's okay!

449
00:28:14.150 --> 00:28:16.027
-I'll get up there soon!
-[Ja-in] Don't leave me!

450
00:28:16.111 --> 00:28:17.821
Just wait there for a second!

451
00:28:22.367 --> 00:28:24.369
[uneasy music playing]

452
00:28:38.091 --> 00:28:40.093
[panting]

453
00:28:48.226 --> 00:28:50.562
[grunts. groans]

454
00:28:53.273 --> 00:28:54.274
[grunts]

455
00:29:00.071 --> 00:29:01.072
[groans]

456
00:29:01.614 --> 00:29:03.616
[child sobbing in distance]

457
00:29:12.208 --> 00:29:13.918
[child sobbing continues]

458
00:29:14.002 --> 00:29:15.837
[child] Mommy…

459
00:29:17.255 --> 00:29:19.257
[child crying]

460
00:29:23.052 --> 00:29:24.095
[An-na] Hello?

461
00:29:25.430 --> 00:29:27.056
Is someone in there?

462
00:29:27.557 --> 00:29:29.476
[child crying continues]

463
00:29:30.810 --> 00:29:34.272
[child] Yes. Can you please open the door?

464
00:29:34.773 --> 00:29:36.107
[An-na] What's your name?

465
00:29:37.817 --> 00:29:39.360
I'm Lee Ji-su.

466
00:29:39.444 --> 00:29:41.029
[Ji-su bangs on door]

467
00:29:41.988 --> 00:29:44.240
Ji-su. I'll open it for you.

468
00:29:44.324 --> 00:29:47.452
I'll be right back.
Just wait a little. okay?

469
00:29:54.083 --> 00:29:55.502
[whimpers]

470
00:30:02.300 --> 00:30:04.844
[man 1] Ugh.
Fuck this fucking rain! Goddammit.

471
00:30:04.928 --> 00:30:06.554
[man 2] How much
do you think this watch is worth?

472
00:30:06.638 --> 00:30:09.140
[man 1] Quit wasting time. We gotta
finish looting before the rain stops.

473
00:30:09.224 --> 00:30:11.559
[man 2] Relax! You could kill someone
and nobody'd find out.

474
00:30:15.438 --> 00:30:16.523
[An-na] Ji-su!

475
00:30:16.606 --> 00:30:18.900
[labored breathing]

476
00:30:20.568 --> 00:30:21.736
Ji-su!

477
00:30:21.820 --> 00:30:23.822
[grunting]

478
00:30:24.405 --> 00:30:25.615
I'm here. Ji-su.

479
00:30:26.157 --> 00:30:28.284
The door. Ji-su!

480
00:30:28.368 --> 00:30:30.370
[water rushing]

481
00:30:32.539 --> 00:30:33.790
[An-na yelps]

482
00:30:37.335 --> 00:30:39.337
[water burbling]

483
00:30:40.213 --> 00:30:42.215
[melancholy music playing]

484
00:31:26.050 --> 00:31:27.385
[thud echoes]

485
00:32:19.270 --> 00:32:21.272
[melancholy music continues]

486
00:32:28.279 --> 00:32:30.490
[gasps. coughs]

487
00:32:40.667 --> 00:32:42.669
[music fades]

488
00:32:48.383 --> 00:32:49.634
[sobs]

489
00:32:52.470 --> 00:32:55.139
[Hee-jo] An-na! Where are you?

490
00:32:55.223 --> 00:32:56.057
An-na!

491
00:32:56.140 --> 00:32:58.017
I'll be right there!

492
00:33:02.981 --> 00:33:04.565
Is Ja-in safe?

493
00:33:04.649 --> 00:33:06.651
[footsteps approaching rapidly]

494
00:33:08.653 --> 00:33:10.488
You better get up here.

495
00:33:14.826 --> 00:33:16.828
[Ja-in gasping for air]

496
00:33:17.578 --> 00:33:20.581
Ja-in. it's Mommy. Mommy's here.

497
00:33:23.584 --> 00:33:25.003
Does it hurt? Huh?

498
00:33:27.547 --> 00:33:30.216
[Hee-jo] Hey. You got his medicine. right?
Give it to him.

499
00:33:31.342 --> 00:33:33.219
Uh. I think I lost it.

500
00:33:34.804 --> 00:33:37.098
Mom. it hurts a lot.

501
00:33:37.181 --> 00:33:39.100
[Ja-in breathing heavily]

502
00:33:39.183 --> 00:33:41.853
Shit. I can't believe this.

503
00:33:42.353 --> 00:33:43.187
[exhales]

504
00:33:43.271 --> 00:33:48.693
Mommy. Mommy. Mom. Mom. Mom. Mom. Mom…

505
00:33:48.776 --> 00:33:49.902
-[An-na] Ja-in.
-[phone beeps]

506
00:33:51.946 --> 00:33:52.905
-Mommy.
-You'll be okay.

507
00:33:52.989 --> 00:33:54.824
-Where you going?
-I'll go find it.

508
00:33:54.907 --> 00:33:58.077
How are you gonna do that?
Let's figure this out on the chopper.

509
00:33:58.161 --> 00:34:00.246
Ms. Gu. Ms. Gu!

510
00:34:00.747 --> 00:34:03.875
Just restore his data to the backup
from when he woke up this morning!

511
00:34:03.958 --> 00:34:05.126
You know you can!

512
00:34:05.209 --> 00:34:08.379
You've got all the data to recreate him.
We've gotta go now!

513
00:34:08.463 --> 00:34:10.506
-[sobs] He's gonna die!
-[Ja-in] Mom! Mom!

514
00:34:13.760 --> 00:34:15.970
Ja-in. just hang in there. okay?

515
00:34:16.054 --> 00:34:18.222
[tense music playing]

516
00:34:18.306 --> 00:34:20.308
[An-na panting]

517
00:34:29.233 --> 00:34:32.070
-[man] Who are you?
-[An-na] I'm so sorry. Excuse me.

518
00:34:32.695 --> 00:34:34.155
Ja-in. hold on.

519
00:34:35.490 --> 00:34:37.492
[An-na breathing heavily]

520
00:34:41.746 --> 00:34:43.623
I. uh. I'm sorry. It's urgent.

521
00:34:43.706 --> 00:34:45.541
[man] Uh. what are you looking for?

522
00:34:47.126 --> 00:34:48.795
[An-na panting]

523
00:34:57.553 --> 00:34:58.554
Ja-in.

524
00:35:01.015 --> 00:35:01.974
Ja-in.

525
00:35:02.517 --> 00:35:04.060
Ja-in. stay with me. okay?

526
00:35:04.143 --> 00:35:05.853
Drink this. Ja-in. Come on.

527
00:35:06.771 --> 00:35:09.398
-[Hee-jo] I'll hold him.
-Keep your hands off! Don't you dare!

528
00:35:09.899 --> 00:35:11.067
Here. Ja-in.

529
00:35:12.235 --> 00:35:15.154
Ja-in. open your eyes. Please?

530
00:35:15.238 --> 00:35:16.364
Drink this.

531
00:35:16.447 --> 00:35:19.742
You gotta drink if you wanna dive
and play with Mommy.

532
00:35:19.826 --> 00:35:20.785
Come on.

533
00:35:22.453 --> 00:35:24.956
Ja-in. Ja-in. Ja…

534
00:35:30.837 --> 00:35:32.964
[children chattering]

535
00:35:33.047 --> 00:35:35.591
-[woman] So you wanna give up Ja-in.
-[child 1] Is this me?

536
00:35:35.675 --> 00:35:37.760
Because of your husband's death?

537
00:35:37.844 --> 00:35:39.846
[solemn music playing]

538
00:35:40.346 --> 00:35:44.183
Technically. Ja-in and I only met
because of work.

539
00:35:44.684 --> 00:35:46.644
I don't think I'm cut out to be a mom.

540
00:35:53.192 --> 00:35:55.278
No one's ever cut out to be a mom.

541
00:36:00.032 --> 00:36:02.493
Emotion Engine has been completed.

542
00:36:03.536 --> 00:36:05.580
Even the Center acknowledged it.

543
00:36:08.958 --> 00:36:11.377
We no longer need
to raise the kids ourselves.

544
00:36:13.212 --> 00:36:14.797
In a few months.

545
00:36:15.548 --> 00:36:17.675
the Center will come to collect Ja-in.

546
00:36:20.720 --> 00:36:22.180
And my Yu-jin too.

547
00:36:22.680 --> 00:36:24.682
[children chattering]

548
00:36:29.937 --> 00:36:32.815
[woman] Maybe we shouldn't have
created them in the first place.

549
00:36:39.488 --> 00:36:41.073
When will that be?

550
00:36:58.507 --> 00:36:59.383
[Ja-in] <i>Mommy.</i>

551
00:37:02.178 --> 00:37:03.262
Mom.

552
00:37:04.055 --> 00:37:04.972
Oh.

553
00:37:05.556 --> 00:37:07.725
Ja-in. Mom's right here.

554
00:37:07.808 --> 00:37:09.227
[music fades]

555
00:37:09.310 --> 00:37:10.853
I peed.

556
00:37:10.937 --> 00:37:12.104
Sorry. Mom.

557
00:37:13.314 --> 00:37:14.315
Good job.

558
00:37:15.107 --> 00:37:16.400
It's nice and warm.

559
00:37:17.360 --> 00:37:18.319
Are you okay now?

560
00:37:18.903 --> 00:37:19.946
[Ja-in] Mm-hmm.

561
00:37:20.029 --> 00:37:22.281
Hey. Mom. can you hug me?

562
00:37:27.328 --> 00:37:30.498
You know.
I got pretty sick because of water.

563
00:37:30.581 --> 00:37:32.792
but I was still so happy.

564
00:37:32.875 --> 00:37:36.712
I got to spend all day with you today
'cause of the water. you know.

565
00:38:10.913 --> 00:38:13.165
-[soothing music playing]
-[birds chirping]

566
00:38:14.333 --> 00:38:16.335
[residents chattering]

567
00:38:19.171 --> 00:38:21.716
[man 1] We're gonna be okay. I'm okay.

568
00:38:21.799 --> 00:38:23.217
[door slides open]

569
00:38:23.926 --> 00:38:26.762
I thought it only stopped for a sec.
but now the sun's out.

570
00:38:28.097 --> 00:38:29.140
[music fades]

571
00:38:29.223 --> 00:38:32.101
You wanna wash the rag. use this.
The water's not running.

572
00:38:32.184 --> 00:38:33.686
[water splashing]

573
00:38:35.021 --> 00:38:36.856
Is it over. or…

574
00:38:39.817 --> 00:38:41.027
[Hee-jo sighs]

575
00:38:41.110 --> 00:38:43.321
I'm wondering what all that panic
and hassle was for.

576
00:38:45.573 --> 00:38:47.241
Ja-in is okay. right?

577
00:38:50.995 --> 00:38:52.872
The head of security called this morning.

578
00:38:52.955 --> 00:38:57.084
The plans had unexpectedly changed
to get you instead.

579
00:38:58.878 --> 00:39:02.590
There's a shelter at the layover point.
We'll be getting off there.

580
00:39:03.758 --> 00:39:06.427
But I heard you're going
to the final destination on your own.

581
00:39:06.510 --> 00:39:08.721
Ja-in can't go since they want him back.

582
00:39:12.391 --> 00:39:15.853
I didn't mention this to you earlier.
did I?

583
00:39:19.648 --> 00:39:23.069
Maybe… you thought I wouldn't come?

584
00:39:26.655 --> 00:39:28.574
I voted you'd come with us.

585
00:39:30.785 --> 00:39:32.244
[solemn music playing]

586
00:39:32.328 --> 00:39:35.122
I have zero interest
in this whole new humanity stuff.

587
00:39:36.540 --> 00:39:40.127
I was just curious to see
what you'd do with Ja-in despite it all.

588
00:39:41.379 --> 00:39:43.881
I mean. given everything.
I figured you'd leave.

589
00:39:45.674 --> 00:39:47.718
Why would you wanna see me leave?

590
00:39:50.805 --> 00:39:51.847
[sighs]

591
00:39:53.057 --> 00:39:56.977
When I was Ja-in's age.
my supposed mother did that.

592
00:39:58.437 --> 00:40:01.273
She cried more than I did.
Said she'd return.

593
00:40:02.024 --> 00:40:03.150
She never did.

594
00:40:04.944 --> 00:40:06.904
Kids carry stuff like that for life.

595
00:40:08.364 --> 00:40:13.536
So I thought seeing you abandon him
might make me feel better about my past.

596
00:40:16.497 --> 00:40:19.041
"Ah. I wasn't the only victim."

597
00:40:20.668 --> 00:40:22.461
"There are more people like her."

598
00:40:23.462 --> 00:40:25.548
"This is just what humans do."

599
00:40:28.592 --> 00:40:32.471
I wanted to see that
on the day the world came to an end.

600
00:40:34.598 --> 00:40:36.934
Some people find comfort
in stuff like that.

601
00:40:37.643 --> 00:40:38.686
[Hee-jo scoffs]

602
00:40:39.186 --> 00:40:41.230
[rumbling]

603
00:40:47.278 --> 00:40:49.780
[residents clamoring]

604
00:40:53.325 --> 00:40:55.327
[deep rumbling]

605
00:41:00.541 --> 00:41:03.752
Shit. Better go now. Let's go.

606
00:41:05.296 --> 00:41:06.213
[An-na] Ja-in.

607
00:41:06.881 --> 00:41:07.798
-Mom.
-[Hee-jo] Come on!

608
00:41:07.882 --> 00:41:10.426
Mom. Mom! Mom! Mom…

609
00:41:10.509 --> 00:41:13.053
Sorry about this.
Thank you for everything.

610
00:41:19.852 --> 00:41:22.897
Aah! Open up.

611
00:41:25.191 --> 00:41:27.193
[rumbling intensifies]

612
00:41:27.276 --> 00:41:29.361
[Hee-jo breathing heavily]

613
00:41:45.836 --> 00:41:46.879
[grunts]

614
00:41:52.760 --> 00:41:55.971
-[Hee-jo] An-na. are you all right?
-Mom. Mom! Mom!

615
00:41:56.555 --> 00:41:58.015
-Mom!
-Let's go.

616
00:41:58.098 --> 00:41:59.850
-It's okay. I'll carry him.
-[whimpers]

617
00:41:59.934 --> 00:42:01.310
Mom! Mom!

618
00:42:02.811 --> 00:42:04.897
[Hee-jo] There. Let's go.

619
00:42:15.741 --> 00:42:18.160
[woman screaming in pain]

620
00:42:20.788 --> 00:42:22.790
[screaming continues]

621
00:42:25.209 --> 00:42:27.336
[screaming continues]

622
00:42:29.547 --> 00:42:31.632
[screaming continues]

623
00:42:31.715 --> 00:42:33.217
[man] Wait. please help us!

624
00:42:33.801 --> 00:42:34.760
[woman whimpers]

625
00:42:35.511 --> 00:42:36.762
I don't know what to do.

626
00:42:38.556 --> 00:42:40.516
-Hey. it's okay. It's okay.
-[groans in pain]

627
00:42:41.892 --> 00:42:44.311
Please help. Please!

628
00:42:44.395 --> 00:42:46.981
Come on! We gotta go now.

629
00:42:49.024 --> 00:42:50.484
[woman groans in pain]

630
00:42:50.568 --> 00:42:51.777
I'm really sorry.

631
00:42:52.820 --> 00:42:54.780
[woman groaning]

632
00:42:55.906 --> 00:42:59.493
Mom. why does that lady feel sick?

633
00:43:01.412 --> 00:43:02.413
[An-na] Uh…

634
00:43:03.372 --> 00:43:04.832
She's not sick.

635
00:43:05.833 --> 00:43:07.501
She's having a baby.

636
00:43:09.295 --> 00:43:10.796
[Ja-in] What about you. Mom?

637
00:43:11.422 --> 00:43:13.132
Did it hurt for you too?

638
00:43:13.215 --> 00:43:15.217
[pensive music playing]

639
00:43:21.765 --> 00:43:22.766
Ja-in.

640
00:43:23.767 --> 00:43:25.978
Can you come down for a minute? Hmm?

641
00:43:26.061 --> 00:43:27.187
[Ja-in sobs]

642
00:43:27.271 --> 00:43:29.690
Ja-in. Mommy's getting tired.

643
00:43:29.773 --> 00:43:31.358
[music fades]

644
00:43:32.234 --> 00:43:33.402
[An-na sobs]

645
00:43:34.069 --> 00:43:36.071
[footsteps approaching]

646
00:43:38.073 --> 00:43:39.867
One more to go. You ready?

647
00:43:43.162 --> 00:43:44.913
-Come on.
-[grunts]

648
00:43:45.873 --> 00:43:47.916
We're almost there! Come on!

649
00:43:48.000 --> 00:43:50.169
Why do I have to leave him behind?

650
00:43:50.836 --> 00:43:54.089
Can't I… Why can't I just take him with?

651
00:43:55.049 --> 00:43:58.594
-Listen. An-na. that's not how this works.
-You said I was going alone. but…

652
00:43:59.219 --> 00:44:01.597
How can I leave him like this?

653
00:44:02.723 --> 00:44:03.557
[Ja-in] Mom.

654
00:44:05.476 --> 00:44:06.435
[An-na] Ja-in.

655
00:44:07.227 --> 00:44:09.521
I'm sorry. Mommy's not angry.

656
00:44:10.022 --> 00:44:12.358
Let's calm down and figure this out.

657
00:44:12.441 --> 00:44:14.818
I also find this whole situation strange.

658
00:44:14.902 --> 00:44:16.904
With the chief researcher
and her kid gone.

659
00:44:16.987 --> 00:44:19.156
Ja-in is the only one left alive now.

660
00:44:19.865 --> 00:44:23.577
That means they'd need him more than ever
to get anything done. right?

661
00:44:24.828 --> 00:44:27.081
There must've been some kind of mistake.

662
00:44:27.164 --> 00:44:28.248
Believe me.

663
00:44:28.749 --> 00:44:30.751
[helicopter whirring overhead]

664
00:44:31.543 --> 00:44:33.545
[ethereal music playing]

665
00:44:34.755 --> 00:44:35.839
[sighs]

666
00:44:41.720 --> 00:44:43.639
[Hee-jo] <i>"July 7th. 8:27 a.m."</i>

667
00:44:43.722 --> 00:44:45.974
<i>"The Darwin Center</i>
<i>will now deliver the following statement</i>

668
00:44:46.058 --> 00:44:49.186
<i>ahead of the rescue operation</i>
<i>for lead researcher Gu An-na</i>

669
00:44:49.269 --> 00:44:51.897
<i>of Emotion Engine Development Team 3."</i>

670
00:44:51.980 --> 00:44:53.732
"First. The unofficial
research institution

671
00:44:53.816 --> 00:44:56.485
under the UN known as the Darwin Center

672
00:44:56.568 --> 00:44:59.988
is committed to doing everything possible
to prevent human extinction."

673
00:45:00.072 --> 00:45:02.616
"Second. Lead researcher Gu An-na
has been appointed

674
00:45:02.700 --> 00:45:05.160
as one of the 49 special task researchers

675
00:45:05.244 --> 00:45:07.663
and will be immediately dispatched
to the temporary lab

676
00:45:07.746 --> 00:45:10.165
to complete development
of the Emotion Engine."

677
00:45:10.249 --> 00:45:13.961
"Third. Lead researcher Gu An-na
will cooperate with all measures necessary

678
00:45:14.044 --> 00:45:16.922
to fulfill the two
aforementioned objectives."

679
00:45:18.173 --> 00:45:19.341
That's everything.

680
00:45:20.217 --> 00:45:21.927
Handing over the appointee.

681
00:45:22.594 --> 00:45:23.804
Okay. Good job.

682
00:45:24.596 --> 00:45:26.932
Dr. Gu. effective immediately.

683
00:45:27.015 --> 00:45:30.811
we're retrieving all data
related to Newman-77 of the Darwin Center.

684
00:45:31.311 --> 00:45:33.313
[solemn music playing]

685
00:45:33.397 --> 00:45:36.108
[no audible dialogue]

686
00:45:43.699 --> 00:45:44.867
What's going on?

687
00:45:44.950 --> 00:45:48.162
Tell them to take those off now!
You said I could go with him!

688
00:45:48.245 --> 00:45:49.163
Uncuff him!

689
00:45:51.081 --> 00:45:52.958
You know. Chief Im Hyeon-mo?

690
00:45:53.584 --> 00:45:56.587
She didn't actually drown.
She ran away with her daughter.

691
00:45:56.670 --> 00:45:59.631
Said she'd rather die
than abandon her own child.

692
00:46:00.132 --> 00:46:01.592
What about you though?

693
00:46:02.301 --> 00:46:04.011
You wanted to give yours up.

694
00:46:06.513 --> 00:46:09.266
You knew this was going to happen
from the get-go. didn't you?

695
00:46:11.226 --> 00:46:12.686
[crying]

696
00:46:12.770 --> 00:46:16.774
This is what humans are really like.
There's no point fighting over it.

697
00:46:17.524 --> 00:46:19.026
Better say goodbye to him.

698
00:46:22.821 --> 00:46:24.072
[sobs]

699
00:46:25.199 --> 00:46:26.992
[man 1] We gotta go. Just get it out.

700
00:46:30.662 --> 00:46:32.289
-[power tool whirs]
-Wait. hold on.

701
00:46:36.460 --> 00:46:39.296
[screams] Are you people insane?

702
00:46:39.379 --> 00:46:40.923
[screams]

703
00:46:41.006 --> 00:46:42.591
Take your hands off him!

704
00:46:42.674 --> 00:46:44.718
Take your hands off him!

705
00:46:46.261 --> 00:46:49.264
I'll kill every last one of you!

706
00:46:49.765 --> 00:46:51.642
[shrieking] I'll kill you all!

707
00:46:51.725 --> 00:46:53.560
[An-na screaming]

708
00:46:55.020 --> 00:46:56.230
Please wait!

709
00:46:56.730 --> 00:46:58.357
Wait! Wait! Please. wait!

710
00:46:59.525 --> 00:47:00.359
[sobs]

711
00:47:00.442 --> 00:47:02.152
Please spare him.

712
00:47:02.903 --> 00:47:05.322
You can't kill Ja-in. You can't.

713
00:47:05.405 --> 00:47:08.367
I promise I'll complete
the Emotion Engine. so please.

714
00:47:08.450 --> 00:47:09.493
[crying] Please.

715
00:47:09.576 --> 00:47:10.577
[man 2] Dr. Gu.

716
00:47:11.328 --> 00:47:13.997
Ja-In turned out wonderfully.

717
00:47:15.207 --> 00:47:16.250
We need him.

718
00:47:16.333 --> 00:47:20.462
If we wanna build another Emotion Engine.
he'll be crucial to the process.

719
00:47:21.296 --> 00:47:22.589
You were the one who said that.

720
00:47:22.673 --> 00:47:24.800
[sobs] Please.

721
00:47:26.176 --> 00:47:29.137
Please. I'm begging you.
Please don't hurt him.

722
00:47:31.765 --> 00:47:32.683
Please.

723
00:47:33.851 --> 00:47:36.144
Take him to the temporary shelter.

724
00:47:36.979 --> 00:47:40.482
Just let me take him
to the temporary shelter at least.

725
00:47:40.566 --> 00:47:41.608
At least that far.

726
00:47:41.692 --> 00:47:45.654
[man 2] Did you really think
there's any shelter after all this?

727
00:47:45.737 --> 00:47:46.822
[gunshot]

728
00:47:46.905 --> 00:47:48.907
[solemn music continues]

729
00:47:50.033 --> 00:47:50.868
[gunshot]

730
00:47:58.709 --> 00:47:59.960
[music subsides]

731
00:48:00.043 --> 00:48:01.044
[man 2] Dr. Gu.

732
00:48:01.128 --> 00:48:02.337
[melancholy music playing]

733
00:48:02.421 --> 00:48:03.714
All of us

734
00:48:05.173 --> 00:48:06.550
are supposed to die here.

735
00:48:07.801 --> 00:48:09.261
You're the only one going.

736
00:48:14.683 --> 00:48:16.685
[melancholy music continues]

737
00:48:43.545 --> 00:48:44.880
[An-na] Ja-in.

738
00:48:52.679 --> 00:48:54.681
[power tool whirring]

739
00:49:14.534 --> 00:49:16.703
[pilot] We need your personal items
for security.

740
00:49:27.965 --> 00:49:29.007
[door opens]

741
00:49:37.683 --> 00:49:38.642
[door closes]

742
00:49:39.142 --> 00:49:41.436
[pilot] Experimental subject data
retrieval completed.

743
00:49:41.520 --> 00:49:42.980
En route to the launch pad.

744
00:49:47.818 --> 00:49:49.528
[music fades]

745
00:50:06.461 --> 00:50:08.463
[poignant string music playing]

746
00:50:13.552 --> 00:50:17.139
[man] Hello. Dr. Gu. I'm Lee Hwi-so.
the director of Isabela Lab.

747
00:50:17.222 --> 00:50:20.726
I'll re-brief you on the mission since
you've joined us on such short notice.

748
00:50:21.685 --> 00:50:24.604
In 15 minutes.
tens of thousands of meteor fragments

749
00:50:24.688 --> 00:50:25.731
will hit our planet.

750
00:50:26.231 --> 00:50:29.651
Upon doing so.
most life forms on Earth will go extinct.

751
00:50:30.944 --> 00:50:34.406
The Darwin Center launched seven rockets
from sites around the world this morning

752
00:50:34.489 --> 00:50:37.242
in our best attempt
to prevent human extinction.

753
00:50:37.325 --> 00:50:40.245
And now.
we are the last remnants of mankind.

754
00:50:40.328 --> 00:50:41.496
[thud]

755
00:50:41.580 --> 00:50:42.956
[Hwi-so] One moment. please.

756
00:50:43.040 --> 00:50:44.249
[thud]

757
00:50:47.794 --> 00:50:49.796
[Hwi-so] Now.
humanity must evolve on its own.

758
00:50:49.880 --> 00:50:52.591
We must survive
the aftermath of the Great Flood

759
00:50:53.091 --> 00:50:55.969
by using the knowledge
and technology we have.

760
00:50:56.053 --> 00:50:58.472
We are aiming to preserve
the smallest unit of humanity.

761
00:50:58.555 --> 00:51:02.768
but our team's immediate objective
is to produce a mother and her child.

762
00:51:03.518 --> 00:51:05.771
We can create human-like bodies
at the Isabela Lab

763
00:51:05.854 --> 00:51:07.856
<i>we're currently heading towards.</i>

764
00:51:07.939 --> 00:51:11.401
<i>but only you can complete the development</i>
<i>of the Emotion Engine</i>

765
00:51:11.485 --> 00:51:13.528
and give them human emotions.

766
00:51:14.154 --> 00:51:16.615
Now. let me tell you
about your mission. Dr. Gu.

767
00:51:17.240 --> 00:51:18.825
We completed the child.

768
00:51:20.869 --> 00:51:23.246
So you want me to make the mother now?

769
00:51:23.830 --> 00:51:25.457
How do you plan on doing it?

770
00:51:25.540 --> 00:51:27.542
[stirring piano music playing]

771
00:51:30.212 --> 00:51:33.507
[An-na] <i>I'll set the mother</i>
<i>as the subject of the experiment</i>

772
00:51:33.590 --> 00:51:35.717
<i>and make the child disappear.</i>

773
00:51:36.927 --> 00:51:39.513
The subject will face
obstacle after obstacle

774
00:51:39.596 --> 00:51:41.306
while she searches for the child.

775
00:51:42.349 --> 00:51:46.019
If she fails. she'll have to start over
from the beginning.

776
00:51:46.103 --> 00:51:47.771
After countless repetitions.

777
00:51:47.854 --> 00:51:50.148
if the subject successfully reunites
with the child--

778
00:51:50.232 --> 00:51:51.483
[Hwi-so] And what if she fails?

779
00:51:53.068 --> 00:51:55.612
Then humanity will face
complete extinction.

780
00:51:55.695 --> 00:51:58.865
[ship rattling]

781
00:51:59.658 --> 00:52:00.700
Dr. Gu?

782
00:52:01.535 --> 00:52:02.911
[woman 1] <i>This is Beagle 6.</i>

783
00:52:02.994 --> 00:52:06.540
<i>Debris of the asteroids hit our engine.</i>
<i>Likely leaking oxidizer.</i>

784
00:52:07.124 --> 00:52:09.000
<i>Can you report</i>
<i>the status from your visual?</i>

785
00:52:09.084 --> 00:52:11.086
[alarm beeping]

786
00:52:12.504 --> 00:52:14.506
[tense music playing]

787
00:52:18.510 --> 00:52:20.512
[music fades]

788
00:52:23.640 --> 00:52:25.642
[water sloshing]

789
00:52:29.938 --> 00:52:30.814
[moans]

790
00:52:30.897 --> 00:52:34.734
[Ja-in] Mom. wake up!
Our house turned into a swimming pool!

791
00:52:34.818 --> 00:52:36.820
[Ja-in laughing]

792
00:52:38.196 --> 00:52:39.197
Ja-in.

793
00:52:39.281 --> 00:52:41.324
[Ja-in continues laughing]

794
00:52:41.408 --> 00:52:44.327
Ja-in. what is this?
What happened to our house?

795
00:52:44.411 --> 00:52:46.413
[Ja-in] The water came in
while you were sleeping.

796
00:52:46.496 --> 00:52:48.039
and it kept coming in!

797
00:52:48.123 --> 00:52:50.417
-[electronic music playing]
-[phone ringing]

798
00:52:50.500 --> 00:52:51.835
-[An-na] Hello?
<i>-</i>[Hee-jo] <i>Are you Gu An-na?</i>

799
00:52:51.918 --> 00:52:54.462
<i>Manager of the Darwin Center's</i>
<i>Emotion Engine Development Team 3?</i>

800
00:52:54.546 --> 00:52:55.672
Yes. who is this?

801
00:52:55.755 --> 00:52:57.883
<i>I'm Son Hee-jo</i>
<i>from Personnel Security Team 1.</i>

802
00:52:57.966 --> 00:53:00.051
<i>I'll be brief</i>
<i>since this is an urgent situation.</i>

803
00:53:00.135 --> 00:53:02.721
<i>-How flooded is your home right now?</i>
-Right now? The water's…

804
00:53:02.804 --> 00:53:03.805
[Ja-in] Mom! Mom!

805
00:53:03.889 --> 00:53:06.516
<i>Listen carefully.</i>
<i>You need to evacuate immediately.</i>

806
00:53:06.600 --> 00:53:09.561
<i>-I'm almost at your apartment now.</i>
-I drew this thing that I saw in my dream.

807
00:53:09.644 --> 00:53:11.271
-Wanna see it?
<i>-Evacuate to an upper floor.</i>

808
00:53:11.354 --> 00:53:13.023
Ja-in. hold on a minute.

809
00:53:13.106 --> 00:53:15.275
Mom. I sent my drawing to your phone.

810
00:53:15.358 --> 00:53:16.818
Come on. Please. Mom!

811
00:53:16.902 --> 00:53:18.653
Do you hear me. Mom?

812
00:53:18.737 --> 00:53:20.864
Why aren't you looking at my drawing?

813
00:53:20.947 --> 00:53:22.949
Ja-in. Mommy's on the phone right now!

814
00:53:23.033 --> 00:53:24.910
<i>Dr. Gu? Are you unable to talk?</i>

815
00:53:24.993 --> 00:53:26.578
No. it's all right. Go on.

816
00:53:26.661 --> 00:53:30.874
<i>Get to the upper floors ASAP.</i>
<i>And make sure to bring Ja-in with you.</i>

817
00:53:30.957 --> 00:53:34.753
In a few months.
the Center will come to collect Ja-in.

818
00:53:34.836 --> 00:53:36.254
And my Yu-jin too.

819
00:53:36.338 --> 00:53:38.423
They're the Center's
most important assets.

820
00:53:38.506 --> 00:53:40.175
So just raise him until then.

821
00:53:40.258 --> 00:53:42.344
When's that supposed to be?

822
00:53:42.844 --> 00:53:43.929
[sighs]

823
00:53:44.971 --> 00:53:49.351
[Hee-jo] <i>Hello? Are you listening. Dr. Gu?</i>
<i>The Center will be collecting Ja-in today.</i>

824
00:53:49.851 --> 00:53:51.728
[tense electronic music playing]

825
00:53:54.856 --> 00:53:57.525
Shin Ja-in. get up right now. Come on.

826
00:53:57.609 --> 00:54:01.029
[Ja-in] But you won't even look at
what I drew this morning.

827
00:54:01.112 --> 00:54:03.990
You never let me do anything I want.
Never ever.

828
00:54:04.074 --> 00:54:06.701
Shin Ja-in. look at Mommy right now.

829
00:54:06.785 --> 00:54:08.578
You have to listen to Mommy. okay?

830
00:54:08.662 --> 00:54:10.997
No drawings or swimming today.

831
00:54:11.081 --> 00:54:13.124
-What about diving?
-No diving either.

832
00:54:13.208 --> 00:54:15.043
You have to stay
by Mommy's side. all right?

833
00:54:15.126 --> 00:54:18.421
If a stranger asks you to come with.
you don't follow. Is that understood?

834
00:54:18.505 --> 00:54:20.048
And if you listen to Mommy today.

835
00:54:20.131 --> 00:54:23.385
Mommy will go swimming and diving with you
next time. all right?

836
00:54:24.094 --> 00:54:25.178
Say something!

837
00:54:25.845 --> 00:54:26.805
Mommy's lying.

838
00:54:26.888 --> 00:54:28.223
What?

839
00:54:28.306 --> 00:54:30.308
Why am I still six years old?

840
00:54:30.392 --> 00:54:31.977
How come I was six yesterday?

841
00:54:32.060 --> 00:54:34.145
And the day before yesterday too?

842
00:54:34.229 --> 00:54:36.523
And the day before the day
before yesterday too?

843
00:54:36.606 --> 00:54:38.733
What are you saying right now?
Just get on my back.

844
00:54:38.817 --> 00:54:40.819
[tense electronic music continues]

845
00:54:48.368 --> 00:54:50.662
Enough! Stop crying!

846
00:54:51.288 --> 00:54:53.206
-Stop crying!
-[man 1] Hey! Get going! Move. move!

847
00:54:53.290 --> 00:54:54.624
[An-na] Excuse me. coming through.

848
00:54:54.708 --> 00:54:56.376
[woman 1] Mommy told you to stop crying!

849
00:54:56.459 --> 00:54:58.378
You understand now! It's plain to see!

850
00:54:58.461 --> 00:55:02.173
It's just as I foretold.
All of this is part of God's plan.

851
00:55:02.257 --> 00:55:05.552
And we must offer a sacrifice
to be forgiven for our sins. Amen!

852
00:55:05.635 --> 00:55:06.511
[all] Amen!

853
00:55:06.594 --> 00:55:08.596
[tense electronic music continues]

854
00:55:08.680 --> 00:55:10.765
[residents clamoring]

855
00:55:11.850 --> 00:55:13.685
[man 2] Go! Hurry up!

856
00:55:13.768 --> 00:55:15.895
-Push!
-[man 3] What are you doing? Move!

857
00:55:15.979 --> 00:55:17.605
-[man 4] Move!
-[man 3] Keep moving!

858
00:55:17.689 --> 00:55:20.066
[all clamoring]

859
00:55:20.150 --> 00:55:21.568
[man 5] What are you doing up there?

860
00:55:21.651 --> 00:55:22.652
[all clamoring]

861
00:55:22.736 --> 00:55:24.154
-[man 4] Go!
-[man 5] Back off!

862
00:55:24.237 --> 00:55:25.613
[man 3] Let's go! Come on!

863
00:55:25.697 --> 00:55:27.699
[all clamoring]

864
00:55:32.329 --> 00:55:33.496
[Hee-jo] Ms. Gu!

865
00:55:34.247 --> 00:55:35.707
Ms. Gu. are you here?

866
00:55:36.416 --> 00:55:37.667
Ms. Gu!

867
00:55:38.168 --> 00:55:40.170
[panting]

868
00:55:41.171 --> 00:55:43.173
[tense electronic music continues]

869
00:55:51.097 --> 00:55:53.099
[dramatic music playing]

870
00:55:56.311 --> 00:55:58.313
[music subsides]

871
00:55:58.396 --> 00:56:00.398
[suspenseful rhythmic music playing]

872
00:56:03.318 --> 00:56:04.736
[gasping]

873
00:56:04.819 --> 00:56:06.363
[residents clamoring]

874
00:56:06.446 --> 00:56:07.447
Ja-in.

875
00:56:08.031 --> 00:56:09.157
Climb up here.

876
00:56:14.454 --> 00:56:15.872
[grunting]

877
00:56:22.379 --> 00:56:24.172
[music fades]

878
00:56:24.255 --> 00:56:25.465
[tense music playing]

879
00:56:25.548 --> 00:56:26.800
Where are you?

880
00:56:32.389 --> 00:56:33.640
Shin Ja-in!

881
00:56:34.307 --> 00:56:35.517
[screaming]

882
00:56:35.600 --> 00:56:37.602
[frightened clamoring]

883
00:56:41.564 --> 00:56:42.982
-[woman 6] Over here!
-[An-na] Ja-in.

884
00:56:51.866 --> 00:56:55.036
[woman 7] Help! Someone help me!

885
00:56:55.537 --> 00:56:56.454
[gasping]

886
00:57:02.043 --> 00:57:03.545
[woman 8] Help me!

887
00:57:08.341 --> 00:57:09.384
[gasps]

888
00:57:11.886 --> 00:57:12.929
Ja-in!

889
00:57:14.722 --> 00:57:15.765
[woman 9] Help!

890
00:57:16.724 --> 00:57:18.726
[helicopter whirring overhead]

891
00:57:45.211 --> 00:57:47.130
[tense music swells]

892
00:57:47.213 --> 00:57:48.089
[music fades]

893
00:57:48.173 --> 00:57:50.216
[Hee-jo breathing heavily]

894
00:57:50.300 --> 00:57:52.510
-[An-na coughs]
-[Hee-jo] Are you all right?

895
00:57:53.386 --> 00:57:55.054
-God. you scared me.
-[coughs]

896
00:57:55.138 --> 00:57:59.142
We spoke on the phone.
I'm Son Hee-jo from the security team.

897
00:57:59.225 --> 00:58:00.935
I need to record this.

898
00:58:01.019 --> 00:58:01.853
[camera beeps]

899
00:58:01.936 --> 00:58:03.396
July 7th. 7:55.

900
00:58:03.480 --> 00:58:06.900
Lead researcher Gu An-na has survived.
but Newman-77 is unaccounted--

901
00:58:07.400 --> 00:58:10.820
Hey. This way.
Chopper's landing on the roof.

902
00:58:11.529 --> 00:58:13.198
My child fell in the water.

903
00:58:13.281 --> 00:58:14.574
Wait a second.

904
00:58:14.657 --> 00:58:16.659
I know where he went. Look.

905
00:58:17.494 --> 00:58:19.078
Caught my eye from how strange it was.

906
00:58:19.162 --> 00:58:21.080
I saw you in that hallway.
Was about to come over.

907
00:58:21.164 --> 00:58:23.875
But I saw a kid going upstairs alone.
That's him. right?

908
00:58:26.294 --> 00:58:27.378
Ja-in!

909
00:58:28.505 --> 00:58:29.714
Shin Ja-in!

910
00:58:34.010 --> 00:58:35.637
[Hee-jo] What do you think happened?

911
00:58:37.055 --> 00:58:38.890
You think someone could have taken him?

912
00:58:39.724 --> 00:58:42.352
I saw him going up by himself
with my own two eyes.

913
00:58:42.435 --> 00:58:44.229
My son would never leave my side.

914
00:58:44.312 --> 00:58:45.438
Ja-in!

915
00:58:45.522 --> 00:58:47.524
[tense music playing]

916
00:58:47.607 --> 00:58:49.025
[An-na] Shin Ja-in!

917
00:58:51.361 --> 00:58:52.320
[Hee-jo] An-na.

918
00:58:53.238 --> 00:58:54.155
We're out of time.

919
00:58:54.239 --> 00:58:55.907
-We have to go.
-Let go.

920
00:58:55.990 --> 00:58:59.202
Look. I'm telling you. we'll find the kid
and bring him to the roof. all right?

921
00:59:00.078 --> 00:59:01.496
[An-na grunts. pants]

922
00:59:01.579 --> 00:59:03.122
Where is my child?

923
00:59:03.998 --> 00:59:05.208
Hand that over.

924
00:59:06.626 --> 00:59:08.127
I won't ask twice.

925
00:59:08.836 --> 00:59:10.421
Where is my child?

926
00:59:14.717 --> 00:59:17.428
An-na. we're gonna die.

927
00:59:17.512 --> 00:59:19.180
Let's just go up first. okay?

928
00:59:21.766 --> 00:59:23.017
What did you do to him?

929
00:59:23.101 --> 00:59:25.603
What do you mean?
I've never even met the kid!

930
00:59:35.488 --> 00:59:36.948
[music fades]

931
00:59:37.031 --> 00:59:40.410
[Hee-jo] Why would I show you the photo
if we were the ones who took him?

932
00:59:43.162 --> 00:59:45.331
But we have to try and find him quickly.

933
00:59:45.415 --> 00:59:46.916
[grunting]

934
00:59:47.542 --> 00:59:50.211
Take my hand. Just take it already!

935
00:59:50.295 --> 00:59:53.381
You asked them to take the kid before.
Then why the change of heart?

936
00:59:54.549 --> 00:59:56.843
If you lay a finger on my boy.

937
00:59:57.760 --> 00:59:58.761
I'll murder you.

938
00:59:58.845 --> 01:00:00.054
What?

939
01:00:00.722 --> 01:00:01.681
[An-na grunts]

940
01:00:01.764 --> 01:00:03.766
[tense music playing]

941
01:00:08.396 --> 01:00:10.607
[Hee-jo] An-na! An-na!

942
01:00:13.318 --> 01:00:15.987
[Ja-in] Mommy! Mommy!

943
01:00:16.070 --> 01:00:17.322
Don't go!

944
01:00:17.405 --> 01:00:19.490
-Mommy! Mommy!
-[gasps]

945
01:00:19.574 --> 01:00:20.825
[Ja-in] Don't leave me!

946
01:00:20.908 --> 01:00:22.952
An-na! Shit.

947
01:00:23.453 --> 01:00:25.747
Just stay right there! I'm coming!

948
01:00:35.423 --> 01:00:37.425
[tense music continues]

949
01:00:45.975 --> 01:00:48.019
[child crying]

950
01:00:57.737 --> 01:00:59.739
[child continues crying]

951
01:01:10.541 --> 01:01:11.834
Is someone in there?

952
01:01:12.835 --> 01:01:15.171
[child] Yes. I'm stuck in here.

953
01:01:17.632 --> 01:01:19.425
Is your name Ji-su?

954
01:01:20.510 --> 01:01:23.221
[child] Yes. How did you know?

955
01:01:24.806 --> 01:01:26.808
[Ji-su crying]

956
01:01:27.308 --> 01:01:28.476
Oh. Ji-su.

957
01:01:28.559 --> 01:01:29.727
Just give me a minute.

958
01:01:29.811 --> 01:01:31.270
I'll get the door open.

959
01:01:31.979 --> 01:01:33.648
[Ji-su] You can just go.

960
01:01:34.190 --> 01:01:38.152
Some guys tried to open it earlier.
but they couldn't.

961
01:01:40.863 --> 01:01:42.949
[An-na] Ji-su. I can open it.

962
01:01:43.032 --> 01:01:44.200
Give me a sec.

963
01:01:48.579 --> 01:01:50.581
[tense music continues]

964
01:02:16.441 --> 01:02:18.651
[Ji-su sobs] Yes. I'm stuck in here.

965
01:02:19.694 --> 01:02:23.197
Ji-su. just give me a minute.
I'll be right back. I will get you out!

966
01:02:23.990 --> 01:02:25.116
Hang in there!

967
01:02:28.077 --> 01:02:30.079
[tense music continues]

968
01:02:33.374 --> 01:02:35.376
[breathing heavily]

969
01:02:37.336 --> 01:02:38.504
[man 1] Fuck this.

970
01:02:44.343 --> 01:02:45.386
[tapping]

971
01:03:07.408 --> 01:03:09.410
[ethereal music playing]

972
01:03:32.391 --> 01:03:33.434
[gasps]

973
01:03:34.143 --> 01:03:36.145
[both gasping]

974
01:03:36.896 --> 01:03:38.898
[music fades]

975
01:03:49.575 --> 01:03:51.619
We'll just have to put these on for now.

976
01:03:51.702 --> 01:03:53.162
We can return them later.

977
01:03:55.623 --> 01:03:57.792
Everyone must have evacuated to the roof.

978
01:03:57.875 --> 01:04:01.629
Your grandpa will be there too.
so don't worry too much. Hmm?

979
01:04:03.881 --> 01:04:06.801
But wait. How did you know that?

980
01:04:07.510 --> 01:04:09.887
That I was on my way to my grandpa's?

981
01:04:14.600 --> 01:04:15.560
Ji-su.

982
01:04:17.436 --> 01:04:18.938
I'm looking for my kid.

983
01:04:19.021 --> 01:04:20.565
He went missing earlier.

984
01:04:23.484 --> 01:04:24.610
Be careful.

985
01:04:31.450 --> 01:04:32.493
[sighs]

986
01:04:40.501 --> 01:04:41.460
Ji-su.

987
01:04:43.629 --> 01:04:46.716
I don't even know why I'm saying
this to you right now. but

988
01:04:48.301 --> 01:04:51.762
once I go out of here.
I'm going to die shortly after.

989
01:04:54.432 --> 01:04:58.644
There's a six-year-old boy.
about this tall. named Shin Ja-in.

990
01:04:59.145 --> 01:05:00.897
If you ever see that boy.

991
01:05:00.980 --> 01:05:03.649
please tell him that his mom
is looking for him. okay?

992
01:05:04.567 --> 01:05:08.654
When I was trapped in the elevator.
I heard something.

993
01:05:09.155 --> 01:05:14.035
It sounded like… some people were
asking a kid some questions.

994
01:05:14.118 --> 01:05:15.328
[uneasy music playing]

995
01:05:15.411 --> 01:05:19.165
They asked him where his mom was.
which unit he lived in.

996
01:05:19.248 --> 01:05:20.958
and if he knew his door's code.

997
01:05:22.001 --> 01:05:22.835
What else?

998
01:05:22.919 --> 01:05:26.964
Ji-su. what else can you tell me?
What kind of people do you think they are?

999
01:05:27.632 --> 01:05:31.344
I was pretty sure they were dragging
something on the floor.

1000
01:05:33.554 --> 01:05:35.806
[distant scraping]

1001
01:05:37.725 --> 01:05:39.727
[scraping continues]

1002
01:05:40.645 --> 01:05:42.647
[metallic clanking]

1003
01:05:47.026 --> 01:05:49.487
Thank you. Ji-su. I've gotta go.

1004
01:05:49.570 --> 01:05:50.947
Please be careful.

1005
01:05:58.079 --> 01:05:59.205
[man 1] Damn it!

1006
01:05:59.288 --> 01:06:01.499
[man 2] Ah. damn! [grunting]

1007
01:06:02.166 --> 01:06:03.793
-[thud]
-[man 3 groans in pain]

1008
01:06:03.876 --> 01:06:05.795
[blows land]

1009
01:06:06.712 --> 01:06:08.589
-[man 2] Fuck!
-[man 3 groans in pain]

1010
01:06:08.673 --> 01:06:10.424
-[man 1] Shit.
-[man 3 groans in pain]

1011
01:06:12.593 --> 01:06:14.595
[uneasy music continues]

1012
01:06:15.179 --> 01:06:16.305
[moans]

1013
01:06:20.267 --> 01:06:22.478
[gasping]

1014
01:06:22.561 --> 01:06:23.729
[gasps]

1015
01:06:25.564 --> 01:06:28.275
-[man 2] Damn it.
-[man 1] Just use this.

1016
01:06:28.359 --> 01:06:29.777
[whimpers. gasps]

1017
01:06:29.860 --> 01:06:31.362
[man 2 grunts]

1018
01:06:34.573 --> 01:06:35.783
[man 3 groans]

1019
01:06:36.534 --> 01:06:38.411
[man 2] You want a hundred beatings?

1020
01:06:39.704 --> 01:06:41.497
[man 1] Hey. that's enough. Let's go.

1021
01:06:41.580 --> 01:06:44.250
[man 2] No. get off!
Fuck. I'm fucking pissed.

1022
01:06:44.333 --> 01:06:47.503
Why the hell did you have to be here?
Now you've turned us into criminals!

1023
01:06:48.087 --> 01:06:49.171
I mean. fuck!

1024
01:06:49.255 --> 01:06:51.173
Why did you leave the door open
if you were home

1025
01:06:51.257 --> 01:06:52.967
and get us all excited like that?

1026
01:06:54.218 --> 01:06:55.428
[man 1] Who are you?

1027
01:06:56.345 --> 01:06:57.638
[man 2] Man. what is it?

1028
01:06:58.347 --> 01:06:59.890
[man 3 groaning]

1029
01:07:07.148 --> 01:07:08.524
Excuse me. sir.

1030
01:07:09.275 --> 01:07:10.943
Sir. are you all right?

1031
01:07:11.861 --> 01:07:14.238
Why don't you just mind your own business?

1032
01:07:14.864 --> 01:07:16.282
Just get going. all right?

1033
01:07:16.365 --> 01:07:17.199
[man 3 groans]

1034
01:07:17.283 --> 01:07:19.285
Hey. what the fuck is going on out here?

1035
01:07:22.163 --> 01:07:23.205
My son.

1036
01:07:24.957 --> 01:07:26.584
What did you do to my son?

1037
01:07:26.667 --> 01:07:28.669
[tense music playing]

1038
01:07:28.753 --> 01:07:30.755
[both chuckle]

1039
01:07:32.048 --> 01:07:33.215
Hey. let's just go.

1040
01:07:33.716 --> 01:07:34.717
All right.

1041
01:07:36.761 --> 01:07:37.887
[Hee-jo] An-na!

1042
01:07:37.970 --> 01:07:40.139
An-na. did you find the kid?

1043
01:07:40.222 --> 01:07:42.349
Over here! Please hurry! These people--

1044
01:07:42.433 --> 01:07:43.809
-[man 1] Sh!
-[man 2] Lock the door!

1045
01:07:44.810 --> 01:07:46.645
[muffled grunting]

1046
01:07:46.729 --> 01:07:47.813
[man 2] Shit!

1047
01:07:47.897 --> 01:07:49.023
[man 1 grunts]

1048
01:07:49.106 --> 01:07:50.483
[muffled grunting]

1049
01:07:50.566 --> 01:07:51.734
-[man 2] Fuck!
-[man 1] Shit!

1050
01:07:51.817 --> 01:07:53.152
[grunting]

1051
01:07:53.235 --> 01:07:54.111
[man 1] Shit.

1052
01:07:54.945 --> 01:07:56.947
[An-na grunting]

1053
01:07:57.031 --> 01:07:58.032
[man 1 grunts]

1054
01:08:00.326 --> 01:08:01.577
[man 1] Shit.

1055
01:08:03.079 --> 01:08:04.538
-Hey. come here!
-[both grunt]

1056
01:08:07.708 --> 01:08:09.710
[An-na panting]

1057
01:08:10.920 --> 01:08:11.921
[man 2 grunts]

1058
01:08:12.671 --> 01:08:14.340
[An-na grunting]

1059
01:08:16.050 --> 01:08:17.093
[Hee-jo] An-na!

1060
01:08:20.387 --> 01:08:21.347
An-na!

1061
01:08:22.098 --> 01:08:23.599
[man 2 yells]

1062
01:08:23.682 --> 01:08:25.518
-[Hee-jo] An-na!
-[man 2] Oh shit!

1063
01:08:27.103 --> 01:08:29.522
-[music intensifies]
-[Hee-jo banging on door]

1064
01:08:29.605 --> 01:08:31.482
[man 2] Why won't you die?

1065
01:08:32.358 --> 01:08:34.360
[man 2 straining]

1066
01:08:36.695 --> 01:08:38.906
[music swells]

1067
01:08:38.989 --> 01:08:40.157
[man 2 grunts in pain]

1068
01:08:40.241 --> 01:08:41.909
Ow! Shit! [groans in pain]

1069
01:08:41.992 --> 01:08:43.994
[grunting]

1070
01:08:44.662 --> 01:08:46.247
[man 1] Ah shit! What the hell?

1071
01:08:47.581 --> 01:08:49.875
Fucking bitch!
Get your shit together. man.

1072
01:08:50.501 --> 01:08:51.418
Get up. you!

1073
01:08:51.919 --> 01:08:53.712
-Come here!
-[An-na screaming]

1074
01:08:53.796 --> 01:08:55.089
-Shit!
-[An-na yelps]

1075
01:09:00.594 --> 01:09:02.596
[whimpers. breathing heavily]

1076
01:09:03.264 --> 01:09:05.516
[door keypad beeping]

1077
01:09:07.143 --> 01:09:08.561
[unlock chime plays]

1078
01:09:10.771 --> 01:09:12.773
[tense dramatic music playing]

1079
01:09:26.370 --> 01:09:27.663
-[music stops]
-[man 2 yells]

1080
01:09:30.082 --> 01:09:31.709
[man 1 yells. whimpers]

1081
01:09:31.792 --> 01:09:33.794
My arm. my arm. my arm! [screams]

1082
01:09:33.878 --> 01:09:36.005
-[Hee-jo] You saw your buddy just now.
-[screams]

1083
01:09:36.088 --> 01:09:37.923
Can't float in water with a broken arm.

1084
01:09:38.007 --> 01:09:39.508
[man 1] This is not what it looks like.

1085
01:09:39.592 --> 01:09:42.052
The kid was alone.
so we were having a little fun.

1086
01:09:42.136 --> 01:09:43.137
[grunts in pain]

1087
01:09:43.220 --> 01:09:46.599
He said he lived on the third floor.
so we let him go. That's all I know.

1088
01:09:46.682 --> 01:09:48.475
-Really.
-Yeah. it seems that way.

1089
01:09:48.559 --> 01:09:50.311
-[bones crack]
-[screaming in pain]

1090
01:09:50.394 --> 01:09:52.188
[man 1 whimpers. screams]

1091
01:09:52.271 --> 01:09:53.647
[water splashes]

1092
01:09:57.318 --> 01:10:00.446
Crazy kids. Hanging out.
breaking into empty units.

1093
01:10:00.529 --> 01:10:02.239
God knows where they came from.

1094
01:10:02.323 --> 01:10:03.324
[sighs]

1095
01:10:03.407 --> 01:10:06.619
Looks like your boy
really disappeared on his own.

1096
01:10:07.912 --> 01:10:10.581
Do you have any idea
where he might've gone?

1097
01:10:11.207 --> 01:10:12.416
I'm not sure.

1098
01:10:13.918 --> 01:10:15.836
He never does stuff like this.
Why would he--

1099
01:10:15.920 --> 01:10:19.506
I see. Well. you were
threatening to kill me earlier.

1100
01:10:19.590 --> 01:10:21.967
but you don't even know why
your boy is missing.

1101
01:10:23.761 --> 01:10:26.972
-[An-na] <i>Ja-in. open your eyes. Please?</i>
-[solemn music playing]

1102
01:10:27.056 --> 01:10:28.307
<i>Drink this.</i>

1103
01:10:28.390 --> 01:10:31.060
<i>You gotta drink if you wanna dive</i>
<i>and play with Mommy.</i>

1104
01:10:31.143 --> 01:10:32.394
Come on.

1105
01:10:34.063 --> 01:10:36.315
Ja-in. Ja-in. Ja…

1106
01:10:37.107 --> 01:10:39.109
[solemn music continues]

1107
01:10:56.502 --> 01:10:57.544
Ji-su.

1108
01:10:58.796 --> 01:11:01.215
I'm going to go. Take care.

1109
01:11:04.176 --> 01:11:08.013
[Ji-su's grandmother] Uh. t. t. take this.
Here.

1110
01:11:16.689 --> 01:11:17.606
Ma'am.

1111
01:11:19.316 --> 01:11:21.318
How did you know about this?

1112
01:11:33.122 --> 01:11:37.084
Ji-su. I really think
you should come with me right now.

1113
01:11:38.585 --> 01:11:40.504
I'm going to be okay.

1114
01:11:40.587 --> 01:11:43.882
I'll stay with my grandparents.
I don't wanna leave them.

1115
01:11:45.134 --> 01:11:47.761
This place will be underwater soon.
You can't stay here.

1116
01:11:47.845 --> 01:11:49.888
But you're the same.

1117
01:11:50.764 --> 01:11:53.350
You wouldn't leave Ja-in behind. right?

1118
01:11:57.104 --> 01:11:58.731
I'll stay here.

1119
01:12:00.274 --> 01:12:02.443
Yes. I can take Gu An-na there myself.

1120
01:12:03.152 --> 01:12:05.988
You're sure we'll be able to find the kid
once we get there. right?

1121
01:12:07.489 --> 01:12:08.365
Yeah.

1122
01:12:09.074 --> 01:12:10.159
Copy that.

1123
01:12:10.659 --> 01:12:12.411
And that temporary shelter.

1124
01:12:13.245 --> 01:12:14.872
What's the exact location?

1125
01:12:16.582 --> 01:12:17.499
Yeah.

1126
01:12:18.250 --> 01:12:20.753
Okay. I have to go.
I'll see you later. Yeah.

1127
01:12:26.050 --> 01:12:27.009
An-na.

1128
01:12:29.970 --> 01:12:32.514
More people from my team
are arriving by boat right now.

1129
01:12:32.598 --> 01:12:35.893
They're professionals. Don't worry.
They can search the entire building.

1130
01:12:35.976 --> 01:12:37.478
Let's make our way upstairs.

1131
01:12:39.021 --> 01:12:40.105
[power tool whirring]

1132
01:12:41.398 --> 01:12:43.400
[solemn music continues]

1133
01:12:44.777 --> 01:12:46.528
I want to find him first.

1134
01:12:46.612 --> 01:12:48.072
He needs his medicine.

1135
01:12:50.366 --> 01:12:51.575
[Hee-jo] An-na!

1136
01:12:52.785 --> 01:12:55.829
Come on. It makes no difference
if you find him first. right?

1137
01:12:56.663 --> 01:12:58.957
I said my team will find him
and bring him up!

1138
01:13:00.626 --> 01:13:02.294
Fine. then explain this.

1139
01:13:02.961 --> 01:13:05.923
You said he'd never leave your side.
So why'd he disappear?

1140
01:13:06.006 --> 01:13:07.674
Be honest. There's a reason.

1141
01:13:07.758 --> 01:13:10.761
Didn't you say you didn't feel confident
about keeping Ja-in?

1142
01:13:14.181 --> 01:13:15.099
An-na.

1143
01:13:15.849 --> 01:13:19.436
You keep going back and forth.
so make up your mind.

1144
01:13:19.520 --> 01:13:22.689
It's your last day with him.
and you know that.

1145
01:13:26.527 --> 01:13:27.694
[An-na sobs]

1146
01:13:30.614 --> 01:13:31.782
That's why.

1147
01:13:32.574 --> 01:13:35.494
That's exactly why
you should let me find him.

1148
01:13:37.037 --> 01:13:39.581
I haven't been able to find him even once.

1149
01:13:41.125 --> 01:13:43.585
There are only a few apartments left open.

1150
01:13:43.669 --> 01:13:45.379
Please help me just this once.

1151
01:13:45.462 --> 01:13:47.798
I'll take the odd floors.
and you take even.

1152
01:13:47.881 --> 01:13:50.342
If you use that staircase.
I'll use this one.

1153
01:13:51.135 --> 01:13:52.469
Please. I'm begging.

1154
01:13:58.058 --> 01:14:01.228
Why keep asking me for help?
We've never met before.

1155
01:14:02.187 --> 01:14:03.188
[scoffs]

1156
01:14:06.859 --> 01:14:08.152
Or have we?

1157
01:14:12.406 --> 01:14:13.907
[breathes deeply]

1158
01:14:22.958 --> 01:14:24.960
[intriguing music playing]

1159
01:14:45.105 --> 01:14:47.107
[music fades]

1160
01:14:47.983 --> 01:14:50.736
[man 1] I don't know.
We've never seen a kid like that.

1161
01:14:50.819 --> 01:14:51.862
I swear--

1162
01:14:54.281 --> 01:14:56.116
[gunshots]

1163
01:15:05.751 --> 01:15:08.420
[Ja-in] <i>Mom. can I borrow</i>
<i>that screen thingy you use for work</i>

1164
01:15:08.504 --> 01:15:09.755
<i>so I can draw something?</i>

1165
01:15:10.339 --> 01:15:13.759
Why do you always wanna draw on that. hmm?
What about your sketchbooks?

1166
01:15:13.842 --> 01:15:17.262
'Cause you never look at it
when I draw in my sketchbook.

1167
01:15:17.763 --> 01:15:19.431
[An-na] What do you mean by that?

1168
01:15:28.273 --> 01:15:30.526
[woman screaming in pain]

1169
01:15:32.903 --> 01:15:35.697
[screaming continues]

1170
01:15:38.867 --> 01:15:42.287
[woman screaming in pain]

1171
01:15:46.583 --> 01:15:49.628
[screaming continues]

1172
01:15:51.088 --> 01:15:53.090
[woman screaming in pain]

1173
01:15:55.592 --> 01:15:57.177
[screaming continues]

1174
01:15:57.886 --> 01:15:59.972
[baby crying]

1175
01:16:00.055 --> 01:16:02.057
[tender piano music playing]

1176
01:16:07.104 --> 01:16:09.106
-[baby continues crying]
-[woman panting]

1177
01:16:22.869 --> 01:16:24.329
[An-na] Here. let me.

1178
01:16:48.312 --> 01:16:55.235
[in Korean] <i>♪ Along the Milky Way</i>
<i>In the blue sky ♪</i>

1179
01:16:55.319 --> 01:16:56.486
[crying stops]

1180
01:16:56.570 --> 01:17:02.034
<i>♪ A little white boat drifting by ♪</i>

1181
01:17:03.785 --> 01:17:10.459
<i>♪ With a single laurel tree ♪</i>

1182
01:17:11.835 --> 01:17:17.090
<i>♪ There sits one tiny hare ♪</i>

1183
01:17:19.468 --> 01:17:26.224
<i>♪ No mast upon the boat ♪</i>

1184
01:17:27.142 --> 01:17:32.481
<i>♪ No paddle to keep it afloat ♪</i>

1185
01:17:33.398 --> 01:17:34.524
[sniffles]

1186
01:17:39.571 --> 01:17:40.614
[in English] Eun-su!

1187
01:17:54.628 --> 01:17:56.171
The water's not too warm.

1188
01:17:56.755 --> 01:17:57.839
I hope it's okay.

1189
01:17:58.757 --> 01:18:00.801
-All right.
-Our baby is so beautiful.

1190
01:18:00.884 --> 01:18:01.885
Yeah. Eun-su.

1191
01:18:03.178 --> 01:18:05.639
Lately. I've been

1192
01:18:06.348 --> 01:18:10.018
having a dream
about a tsunami hitting us badly.

1193
01:18:10.102 --> 01:18:11.228
Right.

1194
01:18:11.311 --> 01:18:13.438
I guess it was a lucky dream.

1195
01:18:16.942 --> 01:18:20.028
Mom. I drew this thing
that I saw in my dream yesterday.

1196
01:18:20.112 --> 01:18:21.113
Wanna see it?

1197
01:18:24.908 --> 01:18:28.578
Mom. I drew this thing that I saw
in my dream yesterday. Wanna see it?

1198
01:18:29.955 --> 01:18:33.542
Please. Mom. Do you hear me. Mom?
Why aren't you looking at my drawing?

1199
01:18:33.625 --> 01:18:35.669
Ja-in. mommy's on the phone right now!

1200
01:18:35.752 --> 01:18:37.754
[stirring string music playing]

1201
01:18:37.838 --> 01:18:39.840
[An-na breathing shakily]

1202
01:18:45.303 --> 01:18:47.055
PHOTOS

1203
01:18:48.682 --> 01:18:49.975
[music fades]

1204
01:18:50.058 --> 01:18:52.018
[breathing shakily]

1205
01:18:53.562 --> 01:18:55.731
[poignant music playing]

1206
01:19:01.862 --> 01:19:03.655
[inaudible dialogue]

1207
01:19:34.102 --> 01:19:35.061
[Hee-jo] An-na!

1208
01:19:36.313 --> 01:19:37.272
An-na!

1209
01:19:38.064 --> 01:19:39.941
I found the kid. Hurry over here.

1210
01:19:41.234 --> 01:19:42.736
[An-na panting]

1211
01:19:47.073 --> 01:19:49.618
Why am I still six years old?

1212
01:19:52.037 --> 01:19:55.957
How come I was six yesterday?
And the day before yesterday too?

1213
01:19:56.041 --> 01:19:59.169
And the day before the day
before yesterday too?

1214
01:19:59.252 --> 01:20:02.088
<i>How long am I gonna stay six years old?</i>

1215
01:20:03.965 --> 01:20:05.967
[music intensifies]

1216
01:20:06.051 --> 01:20:07.052
[An-na gasps]

1217
01:20:40.502 --> 01:20:43.004
[Ja-in] <i>How long am I gonna stay</i>
<i>six years old?</i>

1218
01:20:49.719 --> 01:20:50.971
[sighs]

1219
01:20:54.808 --> 01:20:56.309
[music fades]

1220
01:20:56.393 --> 01:20:57.352
[An-na] Ja-in.

1221
01:21:08.738 --> 01:21:11.491
-[gasps. grunts]
-[ominous music playing]

1222
01:21:20.083 --> 01:21:20.917
[music fades]

1223
01:21:21.001 --> 01:21:24.045
I'll wake you up on the roof
after we find Ja-in.

1224
01:21:24.754 --> 01:21:26.673
You should say your goodbyes at least.

1225
01:21:26.756 --> 01:21:27.799
[An-na gasps]

1226
01:21:31.094 --> 01:21:32.846
There's no point fighting over it.

1227
01:21:36.850 --> 01:21:37.976
You're not…

1228
01:21:38.059 --> 01:21:39.102
[gasps]

1229
01:21:40.645 --> 01:21:42.105
…escaping.

1230
01:21:43.189 --> 01:21:45.150
You died on that rooftop.

1231
01:21:46.234 --> 01:21:48.028
Don't you remember?

1232
01:21:50.947 --> 01:21:52.699
We've met before.

1233
01:21:57.996 --> 01:21:59.205
What was that?

1234
01:22:00.749 --> 01:22:02.542
An-na. what did you say just now?

1235
01:22:02.626 --> 01:22:04.711
[man 1] We'll take care of her.
Please leave.

1236
01:22:05.879 --> 01:22:08.548
Move aside. Hey. stop that! I said stop!

1237
01:22:09.507 --> 01:22:11.760
[man 1] Please board the chopper.
Team lead's orders.

1238
01:22:25.690 --> 01:22:27.609
[tense music playing]

1239
01:22:27.692 --> 01:22:28.693
[gasps]

1240
01:22:28.777 --> 01:22:31.071
[tense music playing]

1241
01:22:32.030 --> 01:22:32.989
[Hee-jo] Hey!

1242
01:22:33.615 --> 01:22:37.035
-[grunting]
-[music intensifies]

1243
01:22:43.458 --> 01:22:44.668
-An-na.
-[unzips]

1244
01:22:45.168 --> 01:22:47.170
[grunting]

1245
01:22:54.177 --> 01:22:56.596
[both grunting]

1246
01:22:58.807 --> 01:23:00.684
[Hee-jo groaning]

1247
01:23:06.564 --> 01:23:07.524
[Hee-jo] Shoot!

1248
01:23:08.650 --> 01:23:10.068
Just shoot!

1249
01:23:15.740 --> 01:23:16.866
[Hee-jo groans]

1250
01:23:17.993 --> 01:23:19.035
[sighs]

1251
01:23:19.119 --> 01:23:20.954
-Good job. An-na.
-[gasps]

1252
01:23:27.002 --> 01:23:28.878
An-na. this. um…

1253
01:23:29.379 --> 01:23:30.797
This'll hurt a lot.

1254
01:23:31.297 --> 01:23:32.424
You'll be fine.

1255
01:23:36.094 --> 01:23:37.512
[gasping]

1256
01:23:39.723 --> 01:23:40.807
[Hee-jo] Look at me.

1257
01:23:41.307 --> 01:23:42.767
You snapping out of it now?

1258
01:23:43.268 --> 01:23:44.352
[gasps]

1259
01:23:44.436 --> 01:23:47.355
What was that earlier?
You said we've met before?

1260
01:23:48.356 --> 01:23:49.357
[sighs]

1261
01:23:49.941 --> 01:23:52.277
[pensive music playing]

1262
01:23:55.697 --> 01:23:56.614
[Hee-jo] <i>So…</i>

1263
01:23:58.783 --> 01:24:00.577
how many times has it happened?

1264
01:24:01.411 --> 01:24:03.955
Ever since I left Ja-in
behind the first time.

1265
01:24:04.039 --> 01:24:06.499
he's disappeared over and over.

1266
01:24:07.000 --> 01:24:08.126
Endlessly.

1267
01:24:09.544 --> 01:24:11.755
And this isn't
the first time we've talked.

1268
01:24:12.255 --> 01:24:13.339
[breathes deeply]

1269
01:24:15.383 --> 01:24:16.885
And I think he knew.

1270
01:24:16.968 --> 01:24:19.721
<i>He knew everything.</i>
<i>right from the very beginning.</i>

1271
01:24:19.804 --> 01:24:21.347
[Hee-jo] <i>So that's why he disappeared.</i>

1272
01:24:22.682 --> 01:24:24.642
Afraid of being abandoned again.

1273
01:24:25.602 --> 01:24:29.064
[An-na] At first. I came to this unit
not knowing it was a trap.

1274
01:24:30.148 --> 01:24:32.108
Later. I came regardless.

1275
01:24:33.777 --> 01:24:36.112
Because from here on out.
I need your help.

1276
01:24:36.613 --> 01:24:38.615
-[tense music playing]
-[gunshots]

1277
01:24:38.698 --> 01:24:40.950
[An-na] <i>When he's upset</i>
<i>or something's bothering him.</i>

1278
01:24:41.034 --> 01:24:42.452
<i>he often hides in the closet.</i>

1279
01:24:42.535 --> 01:24:46.164
And now. there's only one unit left.
He must be on the 30th floor.

1280
01:24:46.956 --> 01:24:47.999
<i>I'm sure of it.</i>

1281
01:24:49.584 --> 01:24:50.460
<i>But the problem is--</i>

1282
01:24:50.543 --> 01:24:52.128
Our security team.

1283
01:24:53.588 --> 01:24:54.839
[rapid gunfire]

1284
01:24:57.675 --> 01:24:59.135
[scoffs] That's right.

1285
01:25:00.428 --> 01:25:01.596
I think I remember now.

1286
01:25:13.817 --> 01:25:15.151
[An-na] <i>And right now.</i>

1287
01:25:15.735 --> 01:25:18.113
<i>they're trying to stop me</i>
<i>from finding Ja-in.</i>

1288
01:25:18.738 --> 01:25:20.281
<i>Just like how they did in reality.</i>

1289
01:25:20.365 --> 01:25:21.199
[gunshot]

1290
01:25:22.450 --> 01:25:24.119
<i>But no matter what I did…</i>

1291
01:25:24.953 --> 01:25:26.162
[gunshot]

1292
01:25:26.746 --> 01:25:27.956
[An-na] <i>I couldn't find him.</i>

1293
01:25:28.039 --> 01:25:29.457
[music fades]

1294
01:25:30.834 --> 01:25:32.168
[intriguing music playing]

1295
01:25:32.252 --> 01:25:33.419
[breathes deeply]

1296
01:25:33.503 --> 01:25:35.672
Their forces are everywhere outside.

1297
01:25:40.385 --> 01:25:41.803
[rapid gunfire]

1298
01:25:53.940 --> 01:25:56.025
Let's go with the same plan as last time.

1299
01:25:56.526 --> 01:25:57.443
No. wait.

1300
01:25:58.736 --> 01:25:59.737
Follow me.

1301
01:26:04.159 --> 01:26:06.161
[both grunt]

1302
01:26:09.497 --> 01:26:10.623
Maybe

1303
01:26:11.875 --> 01:26:14.169
there's no point in doing this anymore.

1304
01:26:15.253 --> 01:26:16.963
Even if I do find him.

1305
01:26:18.256 --> 01:26:20.175
what if he doesn't wanna see me?

1306
01:26:24.512 --> 01:26:26.973
[man] <i>Target spotted on the 30th floor.</i>
<i>Everyone move in!</i>

1307
01:26:31.186 --> 01:26:32.854
[grunting]

1308
01:26:36.191 --> 01:26:37.150
Why?

1309
01:26:38.610 --> 01:26:40.612
Scared he thinks his mom abandoned him?

1310
01:26:41.821 --> 01:26:43.990
If he's disappeared thousands of times.

1311
01:26:44.657 --> 01:26:46.117
it's not 'cause he hates you.

1312
01:26:46.618 --> 01:26:48.745
He's waiting for you to come find him.

1313
01:26:49.579 --> 01:26:52.457
Even though you abandoned him.
he doesn't hate or resent you.

1314
01:26:53.291 --> 01:26:57.921
He'll always be waiting for you somewhere.
hoping against hope you'll find him.

1315
01:26:59.380 --> 01:27:00.506
That's how I felt.

1316
01:27:03.426 --> 01:27:05.345
Go without me. Hurry!

1317
01:27:06.763 --> 01:27:08.264
[gunfire continues]

1318
01:27:21.236 --> 01:27:23.238
[soaring dramatic string music playing]

1319
01:27:33.414 --> 01:27:34.624
[An-na grunting]

1320
01:27:39.295 --> 01:27:41.047
[water rushing]

1321
01:27:48.930 --> 01:27:50.932
[dramatic string music playing]

1322
01:28:24.007 --> 01:28:25.675
I'd really like to see

1323
01:28:27.093 --> 01:28:28.886
what you'll do in the end. An-na.

1324
01:28:31.055 --> 01:28:33.099
That's the whole reason I came. after all.

1325
01:28:53.286 --> 01:28:54.620
[music subsides]

1326
01:28:56.664 --> 01:28:57.749
[An-na gasps]

1327
01:28:59.625 --> 01:29:01.627
[grunting]

1328
01:29:20.730 --> 01:29:22.732
[breathing shakily]

1329
01:29:24.650 --> 01:29:26.652
[thunder rumbling]

1330
01:29:48.883 --> 01:29:51.177
[An-na sobs]

1331
01:30:12.490 --> 01:30:14.117
[sobs]

1332
01:30:19.664 --> 01:30:20.665
[An-na] Ja-in.

1333
01:30:22.208 --> 01:30:24.627
Mommy's abandoned you before…

1334
01:30:25.294 --> 01:30:26.879
[sobs]

1335
01:30:30.466 --> 01:30:32.635
…but Mommy kept on forgetting she did.

1336
01:30:34.429 --> 01:30:37.181
I didn't know about your drawings. and…

1337
01:30:39.225 --> 01:30:41.686
and I didn't know you were hiding here.

1338
01:30:41.769 --> 01:30:43.771
[helicopter whirring overhead]

1339
01:30:46.232 --> 01:30:47.859
Take care. Ja-in.

1340
01:30:52.655 --> 01:30:53.739
Mommy's…

1341
01:30:56.617 --> 01:30:59.120
Mommy's sorry for abandoning you again.

1342
01:31:01.289 --> 01:31:02.540
The thing is.

1343
01:31:04.000 --> 01:31:06.544
Mommy will probably forget it all again.

1344
01:31:06.627 --> 01:31:07.545
[sobs]

1345
01:31:07.628 --> 01:31:09.630
[poignant piano music playing]

1346
01:31:12.091 --> 01:31:13.634
[Ja-in] No. you didn't.

1347
01:31:14.469 --> 01:31:16.762
You didn't abandon me.

1348
01:31:18.514 --> 01:31:21.934
Because. Mom. you told me to wait for you.

1349
01:31:24.395 --> 01:31:25.313
Huh?

1350
01:31:30.359 --> 01:31:32.695
[Ja-in] <i>It was a long time ago. but</i>

1351
01:31:33.362 --> 01:31:35.364
you told me to wait for you.

1352
01:31:36.365 --> 01:31:38.493
You promised you'd be back.

1353
01:31:40.536 --> 01:31:42.371
You whispered to me.

1354
01:31:44.624 --> 01:31:45.541
[An-na] <i>Ja-in.</i>

1355
01:31:46.375 --> 01:31:48.628
Do you see the closet behind Mommy?

1356
01:31:52.423 --> 01:31:53.883
Hide in there

1357
01:31:55.468 --> 01:31:57.470
when you open your eyes.

1358
01:31:58.638 --> 01:31:59.472
Okay?

1359
01:32:00.139 --> 01:32:01.974
Mommy will come and find you.

1360
01:32:03.643 --> 01:32:05.520
But you wait for me. okay?

1361
01:32:06.812 --> 01:32:08.564
[An-na sobs]

1362
01:32:08.648 --> 01:32:10.650
[poignant piano music continues]

1363
01:32:17.156 --> 01:32:18.991
Dr. Gu. are you all right?

1364
01:32:26.832 --> 01:32:27.875
I'll be

1365
01:32:29.335 --> 01:32:30.503
the subject.

1366
01:32:32.630 --> 01:32:34.632
Send mine along with Ja-in's. okay?

1367
01:32:39.512 --> 01:32:41.347
He must be waiting for me.

1368
01:33:16.465 --> 01:33:18.467
[device whirring]

1369
01:33:21.304 --> 01:33:22.179
[An-na moans]

1370
01:33:27.101 --> 01:33:29.854
[Hwi-so] I have informed
the other teams of the plan.

1371
01:33:33.232 --> 01:33:34.734
As you requested.

1372
01:33:35.776 --> 01:33:39.030
we will extract
both your memories and Ja-in's.

1373
01:33:39.905 --> 01:33:41.866
then transmit them to Isabela Lab.

1374
01:33:43.534 --> 01:33:46.829
<i>The experiment will be based</i>
<i>on the transmitted memories.</i>

1375
01:33:47.747 --> 01:33:49.999
<i>If this experiment succeeds one day.</i>

1376
01:33:51.167 --> 01:33:53.628
<i>the new humanity will return to Earth.</i>

1377
01:33:53.711 --> 01:33:55.713
[breathing shakily. sobs]

1378
01:34:15.483 --> 01:34:16.859
[music fades]

1379
01:34:16.942 --> 01:34:18.611
[gunshots]

1380
01:34:26.035 --> 01:34:28.037
[tense music playing]

1381
01:34:36.671 --> 01:34:39.006
[water rushing]

1382
01:34:46.430 --> 01:34:49.558
Ja-in. do you wanna swim
over there with Mommy?

1383
01:34:52.186 --> 01:34:53.646
You can go first.

1384
01:35:04.699 --> 01:35:05.658
Go. Ja-in.

1385
01:35:06.701 --> 01:35:07.952
Mommy will follow you.

1386
01:35:19.380 --> 01:35:20.673
[An-na grunting]

1387
01:35:31.350 --> 01:35:33.519
[ethereal music playing]

1388
01:35:41.944 --> 01:35:43.320
[music fades]

1389
01:35:44.447 --> 01:35:46.323
[Hyeon-mo]
<i>I liked your idea at the briefing.</i>

1390
01:35:47.783 --> 01:35:50.536
<i>Creating emotions through experience. but…</i>

1391
01:35:51.036 --> 01:35:52.455
{\an8}5 YEARS EARLIER

1392
01:35:52.538 --> 01:35:55.624
{\an8}…that'll take too long.
Let's find another way.

1393
01:35:56.459 --> 01:35:58.627
How about we create the baby first?

1394
01:35:59.462 --> 01:36:00.504
A real one.

1395
01:36:01.338 --> 01:36:03.424
with its own thoughts and emotions.

1396
01:36:03.924 --> 01:36:05.676
Five years will be enough.

1397
01:36:06.510 --> 01:36:08.554
[ocean waves crashing gently]

1398
01:36:21.901 --> 01:36:23.903
[baby crying]

1399
01:36:27.531 --> 01:36:30.367
Ja-in. what's wrong. hmm?

1400
01:36:32.411 --> 01:36:33.829
Do you need a diaper change?

1401
01:36:33.913 --> 01:36:35.915
[crying continues]

1402
01:36:36.749 --> 01:36:37.583
Ow. it's hot!

1403
01:36:37.666 --> 01:36:39.543
[ocean waves crashing gently]

1404
01:36:39.627 --> 01:36:40.795
[baby Ja-in coos]

1405
01:36:43.422 --> 01:36:44.673
[An-na] <i>"Ocean."</i>

1406
01:36:45.841 --> 01:36:47.760
<i>"Ocean." Shall we say it together?</i>

1407
01:36:48.344 --> 01:36:49.553
Ocean. together. yeah?

1408
01:36:49.637 --> 01:36:51.305
Repeat after Mommy. "Ocean."

1409
01:36:52.223 --> 01:36:53.349
"Ocean."

1410
01:36:53.432 --> 01:36:55.059
Oh? Then shall we try this one?

1411
01:36:58.813 --> 01:37:00.940
Um! Yum. yummy. Yum. yum. yummy.

1412
01:37:01.023 --> 01:37:04.026
Oh. you wanna take it off?
Ah. kimchi. kimchi.

1413
01:37:04.109 --> 01:37:06.195
-[baby Ja-in groans]
-You want kimchi?

1414
01:37:06.695 --> 01:37:08.781
-Yeah? Ah. yum.
-Mmm.

1415
01:37:13.536 --> 01:37:15.704
Baths are great! Yay. we're done!

1416
01:37:15.788 --> 01:37:16.664
All done. Ja-in.

1417
01:37:16.747 --> 01:37:18.165
[baby Ja-in] Mama.

1418
01:37:23.754 --> 01:37:24.713
Ja-in.

1419
01:37:26.340 --> 01:37:28.092
Can you try saying that again?

1420
01:37:28.592 --> 01:37:29.927
Mama.

1421
01:37:31.512 --> 01:37:32.638
Mama.

1422
01:37:33.931 --> 01:37:35.933
[ocean waves crashing]

1423
01:37:49.738 --> 01:37:51.532
-Mommy?
-Mama.

1424
01:37:52.575 --> 01:37:53.576
Mama.

1425
01:37:53.659 --> 01:37:54.869
[ocean waves crashing]

1426
01:37:59.748 --> 01:38:02.668
Hi there! So you must be Ja-in.

1427
01:38:04.336 --> 01:38:05.421
-Wow!
-[exclaims]

1428
01:38:10.467 --> 01:38:12.303
[crying]

1429
01:38:25.357 --> 01:38:27.359
[ocean waves crashing continues]

1430
01:38:28.360 --> 01:38:30.821
[inaudible dialogue]

1431
01:38:50.132 --> 01:38:51.759
-[ocean waves crashing stops]
-[gasps]

1432
01:38:58.474 --> 01:38:59.391
Ja-in.

1433
01:39:00.392 --> 01:39:02.394
[poignant piano music playing]

1434
01:40:05.165 --> 01:40:06.667
Ja-in!

1435
01:40:54.256 --> 01:40:55.215
Ja-in.

1436
01:40:57.092 --> 01:40:58.927
Do you wanna dive with Mommy?

1437
01:41:00.888 --> 01:41:02.264
I'll count to 30.

1438
01:41:34.004 --> 01:41:38.383
THE GREAT FLOOD

1439
01:41:39.885 --> 01:41:41.595
[ocean waves crashing continues]

1440
01:41:58.237 --> 01:42:01.824
[Ja-in] Mom. Mom. wake up!

1441
01:42:02.574 --> 01:42:05.035
Mom. wake up!

1442
01:42:05.119 --> 01:42:06.537
[ocean waves fade]

1443
01:42:10.707 --> 01:42:11.583
[exhales]

1444
01:42:18.715 --> 01:42:20.717
[dreamy ethereal music playing]

1445
01:42:58.505 --> 01:43:01.967
[Ja-in] <i>Mom. let's dive together again!</i>

1446
01:43:02.050 --> 01:43:04.178
<i>Just like we did yesterday!</i>

1447
01:43:05.554 --> 01:43:08.765
[An-na] <i>You dive. and I'll count to 30.</i>

1448
01:43:11.101 --> 01:43:12.644
[Ja-in] <i>Ready? Go!</i>

1449
01:43:14.563 --> 01:43:15.647
[An-na] <i>One.</i>

1450
01:43:16.857 --> 01:43:17.858
<i>Two.</i>

1451
01:43:18.942 --> 01:43:19.902
<i>Three.</i>

1452
01:43:21.069 --> 01:43:22.070
<i>Four.</i>

1453
01:43:23.447 --> 01:43:24.489
<i>Five.</i>

1454
01:43:25.741 --> 01:43:27.075
<i>Six.</i>

1455
01:43:28.118 --> 01:43:29.286
<i>Seven.</i>

1456
01:43:30.329 --> 01:43:31.371
<i>Eight.</i>

1457
01:43:33.165 --> 01:43:34.333
<i>Nine…</i>

1458
01:43:34.416 --> 01:43:36.418
[dramatic ethereal music playing]

1459
01:45:09.761 --> 01:45:11.763
[dreamy ethereal music playing]

1460
01:46:39.393 --> 01:46:41.603
[music fades]

1461
01:46:42.305 --> 01:47:42.669
